[ Wind Whistling ]

2
00:01:03,461 --> 00:01:05,520
[ Birds Chirping ]

3
00:02:41,960 --> 00:02:45,123
* The hills are alive *

4
00:02:45,196 --> 00:02:49,963
* With the sound of music *

5
00:02:50,034 --> 00:02:52,662
* With songs they have sung *

6
00:02:52,737 --> 00:02:57,731
* For a thousand years *

7
00:02:57,809 --> 00:03:01,006
* The hills fill my heart *

8
00:03:01,079 --> 00:03:05,948
* With the sound of music *

9
00:03:06,017 --> 00:03:07,848
* My heart wants to sing *

10
00:03:07,919 --> 00:03:13,152
* Every song it hears *

11
00:03:13,224 --> 00:03:15,852
* My heart wants to beat *

12
00:03:15,927 --> 00:03:17,792
* Like the wings of the birds *

13
00:03:17,862 --> 00:03:19,853
* That rise from the lake *

14
00:03:19,931 --> 00:03:22,126
* To the trees *

15
00:03:22,200 --> 00:03:23,758
* My heart wants to sigh *

16
00:03:23,835 --> 00:03:26,599
* Like a chime that flies *

17
00:03:26,671 --> 00:03:30,903
* From a church on a breeze *

18
00:03:30,975 --> 00:03:32,636
* To laugh like a brook *

19
00:03:32,710 --> 00:03:34,473
* When it trips and falls *

20
00:03:34,546 --> 00:03:38,312
* Over stones on its way *

21
00:03:38,383 --> 00:03:42,046
* To sing through the night *

22
00:03:42,120 --> 00:03:46,284
* Like a lark who is
learning to pray *

23
00:03:46,357 --> 00:03:48,382
* I *

24
00:03:48,459 --> 00:03:52,361
* Go to the hills *

25
00:03:52,430 --> 00:03:58,767
* When my heart is lonely *

26
00:03:58,836 --> 00:04:02,033
* I know I will hear *

27
00:04:02,106 --> 00:04:07,703
* What I've heard before *

28
00:04:07,779 --> 00:04:12,648
* My heart will be blessed *

29
00:04:12,717 --> 00:04:21,523
* With the sound of music *

30
00:04:21,593 --> 00:04:26,553
* And I'll sing *

31
00:04:26,631 --> 00:04:29,794
* Once *

32
00:04:29,867 --> 00:04:38,138
* More *

33
00:04:38,209 --> 00:04:41,144
[ Church Bells Ring ]

34
00:04:51,684 --> 00:04:52,673
Oh!

35
00:07:32,345 --> 00:07:36,281
[ Singing In Latin ]

36
00:09:08,439 --> 00:09:10,999
[ Church Bells Ring ]

37
00:09:17,448 --> 00:09:20,542
* Alleluia *

38
00:09:20,618 --> 00:09:23,052
* Alleluia *

39
00:09:23,120 --> 00:09:25,315
* Alleluia... *

40
00:09:29,493 --> 00:09:30,892
Reverend Mother.

41
00:09:30,961 --> 00:09:32,155
Sister Bernice.

42
00:09:32,229 --> 00:09:34,163
I simply cannot find her.

43
00:09:34,231 --> 00:09:35,391
Maria?

44
00:09:35,466 --> 00:09:37,900
She's missing from the Abbey again.

45
00:09:37,968 --> 00:09:39,868
Perhaps we should
have put a cowbell...

46
00:09:39,937 --> 00:09:41,097
around her neck.

47
00:09:41,172 --> 00:09:42,571
Have you tried the barn?

48
00:09:42,640 --> 00:09:43,937
You know how much
she adores the animals.

49
00:09:44,008 --> 00:09:46,943
I have looked everywhere,
in all of the usual places.

50
00:09:47,011 --> 00:09:49,172
Sister Bernice,
considering that it's Maria,

51
00:09:49,246 --> 00:09:52,272
I suggest you look
in someplace unusual.

52
00:09:56,520 --> 00:09:57,919
Well, Reverend Mother,

53
00:09:57,988 --> 00:10:00,422
I hope this
new infraction...

54
00:10:00,491 --> 00:10:02,925
ends whatever doubts
you may still have...

55
00:10:02,993 --> 00:10:04,927
about Maria's future here.

56
00:10:04,995 --> 00:10:08,931
I always try to keep faith
in my doubts, Sister Berthe.

57
00:10:08,999 --> 00:10:11,467
After all, the wool
of a black sheep...

58
00:10:11,535 --> 00:10:12,934
is just as warm.

59
00:10:13,003 --> 00:10:14,937
We are not talking about sheep,

60
00:10:15,005 --> 00:10:16,438
black or white, Sister Margaretta.

61
00:10:16,507 --> 00:10:18,941
Of all the candidates
for the novitiate,

62
00:10:19,009 --> 00:10:21,204
I would say Maria is
the least likely--

63
00:10:21,278 --> 00:10:24,076
Children, Children!

64
00:10:24,148 --> 00:10:26,548
We were speculating
about the qualifications...

65
00:10:26,617 --> 00:10:28,050
of some of our postulants.

66
00:10:28,118 --> 00:10:30,018
The Mistress of Novices...

67
00:10:30,087 --> 00:10:32,521
and the Mistress of Postulants...

68
00:10:32,590 --> 00:10:34,023
were trying to help me...

69
00:10:34,091 --> 00:10:37,026
by expressing
opposite points of view.

70
00:10:37,094 --> 00:10:40,530
Tell me, Sister Catherine,
what do you think of Maria?

71
00:10:40,598 --> 00:10:43,795
She's a wonderful girl,
some of the time.

72
00:10:43,868 --> 00:10:45,495
Sister Agatha?

73
00:10:45,569 --> 00:10:48,129
It's very easy to like Maria,

74
00:10:48,205 --> 00:10:50,139
except when it's difficult.

75
00:10:50,207 --> 00:10:52,141
And you, Sister Sophia?

76
00:10:52,209 --> 00:10:54,143
I love her very dearly,

77
00:10:54,211 --> 00:10:57,510
but she always seems to be
in trouble, doesn't she?

78
00:10:57,581 --> 00:10:59,640
Exactly what I say.

79
00:10:59,984 --> 00:11:02,475
* She climbs a tree
and scrapes her knee *

80
00:11:02,553 --> 00:11:04,384
* Her dress
has got a tear *

81
00:11:04,455 --> 00:11:07,390
* She waltzes
on her way to mass *

82
00:11:07,458 --> 00:11:09,153
* And whistles on the stair *

83
00:11:09,226 --> 00:11:11,751
* And underneath her wimple *

84
00:11:11,829 --> 00:11:14,297
* She has curlers in her hair *

85
00:11:14,365 --> 00:11:16,526
* I've even heard her singing *

86
00:11:16,600 --> 00:11:19,194
* In the abbey *

87
00:11:19,270 --> 00:11:21,261
* She's always late for chapel *

88
00:11:21,338 --> 00:11:23,863
* But her penitence is real *

89
00:11:23,941 --> 00:11:26,501
* She's always late for everything *

90
00:11:26,577 --> 00:11:28,772
* Except for every meal *

91
00:11:28,846 --> 00:11:31,144
* I hate to have to say it *

92
00:11:31,215 --> 00:11:33,877
* But I very firmly feel *

93
00:11:33,951 --> 00:11:38,513
* Maria's not an asset
to the Abbey *

94
00:11:38,589 --> 00:11:41,786
* I'd like to say
a word in her behalf *

95
00:11:41,859 --> 00:11:43,724
Then say it, Sister Margaretta.

96
00:11:43,794 --> 00:11:45,352
* Maria *

97
00:11:45,429 --> 00:11:47,829
* Makes me laugh *

98
00:11:50,834 --> 00:11:54,565
* How do you solve
a problem like Maria? *

99
00:11:54,638 --> 00:11:58,904
* How do you catch a cloud
and pin it down? *

100
00:11:58,976 --> 00:12:02,503
* How do you find a word
that means Maria? *

101
00:12:02,580 --> 00:12:03,512
* A flibbertigibbet *

102
00:12:03,581 --> 00:12:04,570
* A will-o'-the-wisp *

103
00:12:04,648 --> 00:12:06,912
* A clown *

104
00:12:06,984 --> 00:12:11,080
* Many a thing you know
you'd like to tell her *

105
00:12:11,155 --> 00:12:14,750
* Many a thing
she ought to understand *

106
00:12:14,825 --> 00:12:17,123
* But how do you
make her stay *

107
00:12:17,194 --> 00:12:18,855
* And listen
to all you say? *

108
00:12:18,929 --> 00:12:23,093
* How do you keep
a wave upon the sand? *

109
00:12:23,167 --> 00:12:27,263
* Oh, how do you solve
a problem like Maria? *

110
00:12:27,338 --> 00:12:33,436
* How do you
hold a moonbeam *

111
00:12:33,510 --> 00:12:38,948
* In your hand? *

112
00:12:40,250 --> 00:12:41,877
* When I'm with her,
I'm confused *

113
00:12:41,952 --> 00:12:43,783
* Out of focus,
and bemused *

114
00:12:43,854 --> 00:12:47,346
* And I never know
exactly where I am *

115
00:12:47,424 --> 00:12:49,255
* Unpredictable as weather *

116
00:12:49,326 --> 00:12:50,884
* She's as flighty as a feather *

117
00:12:50,961 --> 00:12:51,950
* She's a darling *

118
00:12:52,029 --> 00:12:53,018
* She's a demon *

119
00:12:53,097 --> 00:12:54,621
* She's a lamb *

120
00:12:54,698 --> 00:12:56,825
* She'd out-pester any pest *

121
00:12:56,900 --> 00:12:58,765
* Drive a hornet from its nest *

122
00:12:58,836 --> 00:13:02,135
* She can throw a whirling
dervish out of whirl *

123
00:13:02,206 --> 00:13:04,572
* She is gentle she is wild *

124
00:13:04,642 --> 00:13:06,371
* She's a riddle
She's a child *

125
00:13:06,443 --> 00:13:07,569
* She's a headache *

126
00:13:07,645 --> 00:13:09,306
* She's an angel *

127
00:13:09,380 --> 00:13:14,113
* She's a girl *

128
00:13:14,184 --> 00:13:18,280
* How do you solve a problem
like Maria? *

129
00:13:18,355 --> 00:13:22,257
* How do you catch a cloud
and pin it down? *

130
00:13:22,326 --> 00:13:26,092
* How do you find
a word that means Maria? *

131
00:13:26,163 --> 00:13:27,187
* A flibbertigibbet *

132
00:13:27,264 --> 00:13:28,196
* A will-o'-the-wisp *

133
00:13:28,265 --> 00:13:30,358
* A clown *

134
00:13:30,434 --> 00:13:34,302
* Many a thing you know
you'd like to tell her *

135
00:13:34,371 --> 00:13:38,307
* Many a thing
she ought to understand *

136
00:13:38,375 --> 00:13:40,366
* But how do
you make her stay *

137
00:13:40,444 --> 00:13:42,639
* And listen to
all you say? *

138
00:13:42,713 --> 00:13:46,911
* How do you keep
a wave upon the sand? *

139
00:13:46,984 --> 00:13:52,388
* Oh, how do you solve
a problem like Maria? *

140
00:13:52,456 --> 00:13:53,946
[ Door Slams ]

141
00:14:08,806 --> 00:14:16,406
* How do you
hold a moonbeam *

142
00:14:16,480 --> 00:14:17,913
* In *

143
00:14:17,981 --> 00:14:19,915
* Your *

144
00:14:19,983 --> 00:14:23,578
* Hand? *

145
00:14:34,331 --> 00:14:36,731
You may go in now, Maria.

146
00:14:49,337 --> 00:14:51,862
Come here, my child.

147
00:14:57,245 --> 00:14:58,507
Now, sit down.

148
00:14:58,580 --> 00:15:01,413
Oh. Oh, Reverend Mother,
I'm so sorry.

149
00:15:01,483 --> 00:15:03,110
I just couldn't help myself.

150
00:15:03,184 --> 00:15:04,378
The gates were open,

151
00:15:04,452 --> 00:15:06,511
And the hills were beckoning,
and before I--

152
00:15:06,588 --> 00:15:08,920
Dear, I haven't summoned
you here for apologies.

153
00:15:08,990 --> 00:15:11,390
Oh, please, Mother, do let me
ask for forgiveness.

154
00:15:11,459 --> 00:15:13,290
If it would make you
feel better.

155
00:15:13,361 --> 00:15:16,421
Yes. Well, you see,
the sky was so blue today,

156
00:15:16,498 --> 00:15:18,523
And everything was
so green and fragrant.

157
00:15:18,600 --> 00:15:20,329
I just had to be a part of it.

158
00:15:20,402 --> 00:15:22,700
And the bird kept leading me
higher and higher,

159
00:15:22,771 --> 00:15:23,931
as though it wanted me...

160
00:15:24,005 --> 00:15:25,404
to go right through
the clouds with it.

161
00:15:25,473 --> 00:15:27,668
Child, suppose darkness
had come and you were lost?

162
00:15:27,742 --> 00:15:30,336
Oh, Mother, I could never
be lost up there.

163
00:15:30,412 --> 00:15:32,880
That's my mountain.
I was brought up on it.

164
00:15:32,948 --> 00:15:34,916
It was the mountain
that led me to you.

165
00:15:34,983 --> 00:15:36,280
Oh?

166
00:15:36,351 --> 00:15:38,512
When I was a child,
I would come down the mountain...

167
00:15:38,586 --> 00:15:40,781
and climb a tree and look
over into your garden.

168
00:15:40,855 --> 00:15:42,789
I'd see the sisters at work,

169
00:15:42,857 --> 00:15:45,792
And I'd hear them sing
on their way to vespers...

170
00:15:45,860 --> 00:15:48,795
which brings me to another
transgression, Reverend Mother.

171
00:15:48,863 --> 00:15:52,094
I was singing out there today
without permission.

172
00:15:52,167 --> 00:15:54,465
Maria, it is only here
in the abbey...

173
00:15:54,536 --> 00:15:56,766
that we have rules about
postulants singing.

174
00:15:56,838 --> 00:15:58,635
I can't seem to stop
singing wherever I am.

175
00:15:58,707 --> 00:16:01,676
And what's worse, I can't
seem to stop saying things--

176
00:16:01,743 --> 00:16:03,370
everything and anything
I think and feel.

177
00:16:03,445 --> 00:16:05,743
Some people would
call that honesty.

178
00:16:05,814 --> 00:16:07,645
But it's terrible,
Reverend Mother.

179
00:16:07,716 --> 00:16:10,617
You know how Sister Berthe
always makes me kiss the floor...

180
00:16:10,685 --> 00:16:12,619
after we've had a disagreement?

181
00:16:12,687 --> 00:16:16,282
Lately I've taken to kissing
the floor when I see her coming

182
00:16:16,358 --> 00:16:18,292
just to save time.

183
00:16:18,360 --> 00:16:21,796
Maria, when you saw us
over the abbey wall

184
00:16:21,863 --> 00:16:24,627
and longed to be one of us,

185
00:16:24,699 --> 00:16:26,633
that didn't necessarily mean

186
00:16:26,701 --> 00:16:27,725
that you were prepared

187
00:16:27,802 --> 00:16:29,133
for the way we live here, did it?

188
00:16:30,472 --> 00:16:33,737
No, Mother, but I pray, and I try,

189
00:16:33,808 --> 00:16:35,639
and I am learning. I really am.

190
00:16:35,710 --> 00:16:36,734
What is the most important lesson

191
00:16:36,811 --> 00:16:37,743
you have learned here, my child?

192
00:16:37,812 --> 00:16:40,212
To find out what
is the will of God

193
00:16:40,281 --> 00:16:42,181
and to do it
wholeheartedly.

194
00:16:44,352 --> 00:16:46,149
Maria...

195
00:16:46,221 --> 00:16:49,156
it seems to be the will of God

196
00:16:49,224 --> 00:16:50,418
that you leave us.

197
00:16:50,492 --> 00:16:52,221
- Leave you?
- Only for a while, Maria.

198
00:16:52,293 --> 00:16:55,228
Oh, no, please, Don't do that.
Don't send me away.

199
00:16:55,296 --> 00:16:57,992
This is where I belong.
It's my home, my family.

200
00:16:58,066 --> 00:16:59,556
It's my life.

201
00:16:59,634 --> 00:17:01,534
But are you truly ready for it?

202
00:17:01,603 --> 00:17:03,298
Yes, I am.

203
00:17:03,371 --> 00:17:05,464
Perhaps if you go
out into the world

204
00:17:05,540 --> 00:17:06,564
for a time,

205
00:17:06,641 --> 00:17:08,074
knowing what we
expect of you,

206
00:17:08,143 --> 00:17:10,077
You will have
a chance to find out

207
00:17:10,145 --> 00:17:11,373
if you could expect it
of yourself.

208
00:17:11,446 --> 00:17:14,040
I know what you expect,
mother, and I can do it.

209
00:17:14,115 --> 00:17:14,877
I promise I can.

210
00:17:14,949 --> 00:17:15,881
Maria.

211
00:17:19,421 --> 00:17:20,786
Yes, Mother...

212
00:17:22,157 --> 00:17:25,058
If it is God's will.

213
00:17:25,126 --> 00:17:29,187
there is a family near Salzburg

214
00:17:29,264 --> 00:17:31,698
that needs a governess
until September.

215
00:17:31,766 --> 00:17:32,698
September?

216
00:17:32,767 --> 00:17:34,200
To take care of seven children.

217
00:17:34,269 --> 00:17:35,896
Seven children!

218
00:17:35,970 --> 00:17:37,403
Do you like children, Maria?

219
00:17:37,472 --> 00:17:39,997
Well, yes, but seven!

220
00:17:40,075 --> 00:17:42,407
I will tell Captain von Trapp

221
00:17:42,477 --> 00:17:44,342
to expect you tomorrow.

222
00:17:44,412 --> 00:17:46,175
Uh, Captain?

223
00:17:46,247 --> 00:17:49,648
A retired officer of
the Imperial Navy.

224
00:17:49,717 --> 00:17:51,184
a fine man and a brave one.

225
00:17:51,252 --> 00:17:53,345
His wife died several years ago,

226
00:17:53,421 --> 00:17:54,752
leaving him alone
with the children.

227
00:17:54,823 --> 00:17:56,814
I understand he's had
a most difficult time

228
00:17:56,891 --> 00:17:59,257
managing to keep
a governess there.

229
00:17:59,327 --> 00:18:02,387
Uh, why difficult,
Reverend Mother?

230
00:18:02,464 --> 00:18:06,628
The Lord will show you
in his own good time.

231
00:18:43,438 --> 00:18:46,168
When The Lord closes a door,

232
00:18:46,241 --> 00:18:48,368
somewhere he opens a window.

233
00:18:51,179 --> 00:18:56,412
* What will this day be like? *

234
00:18:56,484 --> 00:18:58,509
* I wonder *

235
00:19:05,193 --> 00:19:09,994
* What will my future be? *

236
00:19:10,064 --> 00:19:12,532
* I wonder *

237
00:19:14,068 --> 00:19:17,162
* It could be so exciting *

238
00:19:17,238 --> 00:19:18,671
* To be out in the world *

239
00:19:18,740 --> 00:19:20,503
* To be free *

240
00:19:20,575 --> 00:19:24,568
* My heart should
be wildly rejoicing *

241
00:19:24,646 --> 00:19:30,209
* Oh, what's
the matter with me? *

242
00:19:30,285 --> 00:19:33,721
* I have always
longed for adventure *

243
00:19:33,788 --> 00:19:37,554
* To do the things
I've never dared *

244
00:19:37,625 --> 00:19:40,992
* Now here
I'm facing adventure *

245
00:19:41,062 --> 00:19:42,927
* Then why *

246
00:19:42,997 --> 00:19:47,331
* Am I so scared? *

247
00:19:50,572 --> 00:19:53,837
* A Captain
with seven children *

248
00:19:53,908 --> 00:19:56,001
* What's so fearsome
about that? *

249
00:19:58,079 --> 00:20:02,015
* Oh, I must stop these doubts,
all these worries *

250
00:20:02,083 --> 00:20:05,018
* If I don't, I just know
I'll turn back *

251
00:20:05,086 --> 00:20:09,523
* I must dream
of the things I am seeking *

252
00:20:09,591 --> 00:20:12,355
* I am seeking
the courage *

253
00:20:12,427 --> 00:20:15,055
* I lack *

254
00:20:15,129 --> 00:20:19,361
* The courage to
serve them with reliance *

255
00:20:19,434 --> 00:20:22,528
* Face my mistakes
without defiance *

256
00:20:22,604 --> 00:20:24,367
* Show them I'm worthy *

257
00:20:24,439 --> 00:20:27,374
* And while I show them *

258
00:20:27,442 --> 00:20:28,875
* I'll *

259
00:20:28,943 --> 00:20:30,035
* Show *

260
00:20:30,111 --> 00:20:31,703
* Me *

261
00:20:31,779 --> 00:20:33,212
* So *

262
00:20:33,281 --> 00:20:37,047
* Let them bring on
all their problems *

263
00:20:37,118 --> 00:20:40,713
* I'll do better
than my best *

264
00:20:40,788 --> 00:20:41,880
* I have confidence *

265
00:20:41,956 --> 00:20:43,890
* They'll put me
to the test *

266
00:20:43,958 --> 00:20:47,325
* But I'll make them see
I have confidence in me *

267
00:20:47,395 --> 00:20:51,058
* Somehow
I will impress them *

268
00:20:51,132 --> 00:20:54,568
* I will be
firm but kind *

269
00:20:54,636 --> 00:20:56,729
* And all those children *

270
00:20:56,804 --> 00:20:58,237
* Heaven bless them *

271
00:20:58,306 --> 00:21:01,503
* They will look up to me
and mind me *

272
00:21:01,576 --> 00:21:05,068
* With each step,
I am more certain *

273
00:21:05,146 --> 00:21:08,582
* Everything
will turn out fine *

274
00:21:08,650 --> 00:21:11,915
* I have confidence
the world can all be mine *

275
00:21:11,986 --> 00:21:13,248
* They'll have to agree *

276
00:21:13,321 --> 00:21:17,417
* I have
confidence in me *

277
00:21:18,826 --> 00:21:22,091
* I have confidence
in sunshine *

278
00:21:22,163 --> 00:21:25,257
* I have confidence
in rain *

279
00:21:25,333 --> 00:21:28,427
* I have confidence that
spring will come again *

280
00:21:28,503 --> 00:21:29,765
* Besides which, you see *

281
00:21:29,837 --> 00:21:31,930
* I have
confidence in me *

282
00:21:32,006 --> 00:21:35,271
* Strength doesn't
lie in numbers *

283
00:21:35,343 --> 00:21:38,437
* Strength doesn't
lie in wealth *

284
00:21:38,513 --> 00:21:41,949
* Strength lies in nights
of peaceful slumbers *

285
00:21:42,016 --> 00:21:44,109
* When you wake up,
wake up *

286
00:21:44,185 --> 00:21:48,281
* It's healthy, all I trust
I leave my heart to *

287
00:21:48,356 --> 00:21:51,621
* All I trust
becomes my own *

288
00:21:51,693 --> 00:21:54,787
* I have confidence
in confidence *

289
00:21:54,862 --> 00:21:56,454
* Alone... *

290
00:22:09,825 --> 00:22:11,918
Oh, help.

291
00:22:24,840 --> 00:22:27,434
* I have confidence *

292
00:22:27,509 --> 00:22:31,946
* In confidence alone *

293
00:22:32,014 --> 00:22:34,608
* Besides which, you see *

294
00:22:34,683 --> 00:22:37,277
* I have confidence *

295
00:22:37,352 --> 00:22:44,451
* In me *

296
00:22:44,526 --> 00:22:46,460
[ Doorbell Rings ]

297
00:22:46,528 --> 00:22:47,790
Oh!

298
00:22:50,532 --> 00:22:52,557
Hello! Here I am.

299
00:22:54,136 --> 00:22:55,467
I'm from
the convent.

300
00:22:55,537 --> 00:22:57,664
I'm the new
governess, Captain.

301
00:22:57,739 --> 00:23:01,231
And I'm the old
butler, fraulein.

302
00:23:02,644 --> 00:23:05,112
Oh. Well,
how do you do?

303
00:23:07,649 --> 00:23:08,673
Hmm...

304
00:23:16,391 --> 00:23:20,157
You'll, uh,
wait here, please.

305
00:24:30,799 --> 00:24:32,232
[ Door Opens ]

306
00:24:46,848 --> 00:24:48,247
In the future,
you'll kindly remember

307
00:24:48,316 --> 00:24:49,613
there are certain rooms
in this house

308
00:24:49,684 --> 00:24:50,742
which are not
to be disturbed.

309
00:24:51,820 --> 00:24:54,015
Yes, Captain, sir.

310
00:25:00,495 --> 00:25:03,157
And why do you stare
at me that way?

311
00:25:03,231 --> 00:25:07,327
You don't look at all
like a sea captain, sir.

312
00:25:07,402 --> 00:25:10,565
I'm afraid you don't look
very much like a governess.

313
00:25:10,639 --> 00:25:12,163
Turn around, please.

314
00:25:12,240 --> 00:25:13,434
What?

315
00:25:13,508 --> 00:25:15,203
Turn.

316
00:25:17,579 --> 00:25:19,137
Hat off.

317
00:25:22,117 --> 00:25:23,914
It's the dress. You'll have
to put on another one

318
00:25:23,985 --> 00:25:25,282
before you meet
the children.

319
00:25:25,353 --> 00:25:26,342
But I don't have
another one.

320
00:25:26,421 --> 00:25:28,514
When we entered
the abbey,

321
00:25:28,590 --> 00:25:29,750
our worldly clothes
were given to the poor.

322
00:25:29,825 --> 00:25:30,814
What about this one?

323
00:25:30,892 --> 00:25:33,224
The poor didn't
want this one.

324
00:25:33,295 --> 00:25:34,694
Hmm.

325
00:25:34,763 --> 00:25:36,390
I would have made
myself a new dress,

326
00:25:36,464 --> 00:25:37,453
but there wasn't time.

327
00:25:37,532 --> 00:25:38,556
I can make
my own clothes.

328
00:25:38,633 --> 00:25:42,160
Well, I'll see that you
get some material.

329
00:25:42,237 --> 00:25:44,364
Today, if possible.

330
00:25:44,439 --> 00:25:45,997
Now, fraulein...

331
00:25:46,074 --> 00:25:47,234
Maria.

332
00:25:47,309 --> 00:25:48,742
Fraulein Maria,
I don't know how much

333
00:25:48,810 --> 00:25:50,175
the Mother Abbess
has told you.

334
00:25:50,245 --> 00:25:51,678
Not much.

335
00:25:51,746 --> 00:25:52,872
You're the 1 2th in
a long line of governesses

336
00:25:52,948 --> 00:25:54,006
who have come to look
after my children

337
00:25:54,082 --> 00:25:55,572
since their mother died.

338
00:25:55,650 --> 00:25:58,141
I trust that you will be an
improvement on the last one.

339
00:25:58,220 --> 00:26:00,085
She stayed only two hours.

340
00:26:00,155 --> 00:26:03,249
What's wrong
with the children, sir?

341
00:26:03,325 --> 00:26:07,022
There's nothing wrong
with the children,

342
00:26:07,095 --> 00:26:08,858
only the governesses.

343
00:26:10,432 --> 00:26:11,990
They were completely unable
to maintain discipline.

344
00:26:12,067 --> 00:26:13,295
Without it, this house
cannot be properly run.

345
00:26:13,368 --> 00:26:14,733
Will you please
remember that, fraulein?

346
00:26:14,803 --> 00:26:16,100
Yes, sir.

347
00:26:16,171 --> 00:26:18,036
Every morning you will drill
the children in their studies.

348
00:26:18,106 --> 00:26:21,542
I will not permit them to dream
away their summer holidays.

349
00:26:21,610 --> 00:26:23,737
Each afternoon they will
march about the grounds,

350
00:26:23,812 --> 00:26:24,972
breathing deeply.

351
00:26:25,046 --> 00:26:26,536
Bedtime is to be strictly
observed, no exceptions.

352
00:26:26,615 --> 00:26:28,549
Excuse me, sir,
when do they play?

353
00:26:28,617 --> 00:26:29,948
You will see to it that
they conduct themselves

354
00:26:30,018 --> 00:26:32,248
at all time with the utmost
orderliness and decorum.

355
00:26:32,320 --> 00:26:33,412
I'm placing you in command.

356
00:26:33,488 --> 00:26:34,750
Yes, sir!

357
00:26:37,525 --> 00:26:39,288
[ Whistle Blows ]

358
00:26:42,430 --> 00:26:44,625
[ Whistle Blows ]

359
00:26:44,699 --> 00:26:46,633
[ Running Footsteps ]

360
00:26:59,581 --> 00:27:01,640
[ Blowing Whistle ]

361
00:27:55,170 --> 00:27:59,436
Now, this is your new
governess, Fraulein Maria.

362
00:28:01,443 --> 00:28:03,411
As I sound your signals,

363
00:28:03,478 --> 00:28:04,638
You will step forward
and give your name.

364
00:28:04,713 --> 00:28:06,010
You, fraulein,
will listen carefully.

365
00:28:06,081 --> 00:28:08,049
Learn those signals so you can
call them when you want them.

366
00:28:08,116 --> 00:28:09,378
[ Blowing Whistle ]

367
00:28:09,451 --> 00:28:11,442
Liesl.

368
00:28:11,519 --> 00:28:13,282
Friedrich.

369
00:28:13,355 --> 00:28:15,118
Louisa.

370
00:28:15,190 --> 00:28:16,623
Kurt.

371
00:28:16,691 --> 00:28:17,953
Brigitta.

372
00:28:18,026 --> 00:28:19,493
Marta.

373
00:28:19,561 --> 00:28:20,493
[ Blows Whistle ]

374
00:28:21,563 --> 00:28:22,495
[ Blows Whistle ]

375
00:28:25,700 --> 00:28:27,793
And Gretl. Ahem.

376
00:28:31,406 --> 00:28:34,307
Now, let's see
how well you listened.

377
00:28:34,376 --> 00:28:38,142
Oh, I won't need to whistle
for them, Reverend Captain.

378
00:28:38,213 --> 00:28:42,650
I mean, I'll use their names.
and such lovely names.

379
00:28:42,717 --> 00:28:44,207
[ von Trapp ]
Fraulein, this is a large house.

380
00:28:44,285 --> 00:28:45,582
The grounds
are very extensive,

381
00:28:45,653 --> 00:28:48,486
and I will not have
anyone shouting.

382
00:28:48,556 --> 00:28:50,319
Take this, please.
learn to use it.

383
00:28:50,392 --> 00:28:52,292
The children
will help you.

384
00:28:54,062 --> 00:28:57,327
Now, when I want you,
this is what you will hear.

385
00:28:57,399 --> 00:28:58,423
[ Whistle Blows ]

386
00:28:58,500 --> 00:29:01,025
No, sir. I'm sorry, sir.

387
00:29:01,102 --> 00:29:03,570
I could never answer
to a whistle.

388
00:29:03,638 --> 00:29:05,572
Whistles are for dogs
and cats and other animals,

389
00:29:05,640 --> 00:29:08,074
but not for children,
and definitely not for me.

390
00:29:08,143 --> 00:29:10,270
It would be
too humiliating.

391
00:29:11,813 --> 00:29:17,513
Fraulein, were you this
much trouble at the abbey?

392
00:29:17,585 --> 00:29:18,950
Oh, much more, sir.

393
00:29:19,020 --> 00:29:20,749
Hmm...

394
00:29:23,825 --> 00:29:25,588
[ Whistle Blows ]

395
00:29:29,397 --> 00:29:31,627
Excuse me, sir.
I don't know your signal?

396
00:29:31,699 --> 00:29:35,032
You may call me
Captain.

397
00:29:47,813 --> 00:29:49,246
At ease.

398
00:29:51,984 --> 00:29:54,248
Well, now that
there's just us,

399
00:29:54,319 --> 00:29:56,048
Would you please tell me
all your names again

400
00:29:56,121 --> 00:29:58,419
And how old you are?

401
00:29:58,490 --> 00:30:00,924
I'm Liesl.
I'm 1 6 years old,

402
00:30:00,993 --> 00:30:03,188
and I don't need
a governess.

403
00:30:03,262 --> 00:30:07,028
I'm glad you told me, Liesl.
We'll just be good friends.

404
00:30:07,099 --> 00:30:12,765
I'm Friedrich.
I'm 1 4. I'm impossible.

405
00:30:12,838 --> 00:30:14,738
Really? Who told you
that, Friedrich?

406
00:30:14,806 --> 00:30:18,708
Fraulein Josephine,
four governesses ago.

407
00:30:18,777 --> 00:30:20,972
I'm Brigitta.

408
00:30:21,046 --> 00:30:25,415
You, um, didn't tell me
how old you are, Louisa.

409
00:30:25,484 --> 00:30:27,384
I'm Brigitta.

410
00:30:27,452 --> 00:30:30,046
She's Louisa.
She's 1 3 years old,

411
00:30:30,122 --> 00:30:31,555
and you're smart.

412
00:30:31,623 --> 00:30:33,955
I'm 1 0, and I think
your dress

413
00:30:34,026 --> 00:30:36,392
is the ugliest one
I ever saw.

414
00:30:36,461 --> 00:30:38,656
Brigitta, you
shouldn't say that.

415
00:30:38,730 --> 00:30:41,164
Why not? Don't you
think it's ugly?

416
00:30:41,233 --> 00:30:44,168
Of course, but Fraulein
Hilda's was ugliest.

417
00:30:44,236 --> 00:30:47,728
I'm Kurt. I'm 1 1 .
I'm incorrigible.

418
00:30:47,806 --> 00:30:49,068
Congratulations.

419
00:30:49,141 --> 00:30:51,075
What's
incorrigible?

420
00:30:51,143 --> 00:30:53,077
I think it means

421
00:30:53,145 --> 00:30:55,943
you want to be
treated like a boy.

422
00:30:56,014 --> 00:30:56,503
Mm-hmm?

423
00:30:56,581 --> 00:30:58,071
I'm Marta,

424
00:30:58,150 --> 00:31:00,243
and I'm gonna be 7
on Tuesday.

425
00:31:00,319 --> 00:31:01,809
And I'd like
a pink parasol.

426
00:31:01,887 --> 00:31:04,583
Well, pink's my
favorite color, too.

427
00:31:04,656 --> 00:31:06,248
[ Stomp, Stomp ]

428
00:31:06,325 --> 00:31:08,088
Yes, you're Gretl,

429
00:31:08,160 --> 00:31:10,754
and you're
five years old?

430
00:31:10,829 --> 00:31:12,296
My, you're
practically a lady.

431
00:31:14,232 --> 00:31:16,097
Now I have
to tell you a secret--

432
00:31:16,168 --> 00:31:18,693
I've never been
a governess before.

433
00:31:20,005 --> 00:31:21,165
You mean you don't
know anything

434
00:31:21,239 --> 00:31:22,365
about being
a governess?

435
00:31:22,441 --> 00:31:24,534
Nothing. I'll need
lots of advice.

436
00:31:24,609 --> 00:31:27,874
Well, the best way
to start is to be sure

437
00:31:27,946 --> 00:31:29,436
to tell father to mind
his own business.

438
00:31:29,514 --> 00:31:32,278
You must never come
to dinner on time.

439
00:31:32,351 --> 00:31:34,285
Never eat
soup quietly.

440
00:31:34,353 --> 00:31:35,445
[ Slurp ]

441
00:31:35,520 --> 00:31:36,680
And during
dessert,

442
00:31:36,755 --> 00:31:38,017
always blow
your nose.

443
00:31:38,090 --> 00:31:40,285
Don't you believe a word
they say, fraulein.

444
00:31:40,359 --> 00:31:41,621
Why not?

445
00:31:41,693 --> 00:31:44,526
- Because I like you!
- [ Clapping ]

446
00:31:44,596 --> 00:31:46,461
All right, children,
outside for your walk.

447
00:31:46,531 --> 00:31:47,964
Father's orders.

448
00:31:48,033 --> 00:31:49,967
Now, hurry up, hurry up.
Quick, quick, quick!

449
00:31:50,035 --> 00:31:51,662
Fraulein Maria,

450
00:31:51,737 --> 00:31:53,364
I'm Frau Schmidt,
the housekeeper.

451
00:31:53,438 --> 00:31:54,462
How do you do?

452
00:31:54,539 --> 00:31:55,733
How do you do?

453
00:31:55,807 --> 00:31:58,207
I'll show you
to your room.
Follow me.

454
00:32:08,887 --> 00:32:10,320
Poor little dears.

455
00:32:13,625 --> 00:32:18,255
Ah! Aah! Aah! Oh!

456
00:32:22,534 --> 00:32:24,331
- Oh--
- You're very lucky.

457
00:32:24,403 --> 00:32:28,100
with Fraulein Helga,
it was a snake.

458
00:32:42,054 --> 00:32:43,681
Good evening.

459
00:32:43,755 --> 00:32:45,689
Good evening,
children.

460
00:32:45,757 --> 00:32:47,554
Good evening,
Fraulein Maria.

461
00:32:47,626 --> 00:32:49,526
Aah!

462
00:32:55,200 --> 00:32:57,168
Enchanting
little ritual.

463
00:32:57,235 --> 00:33:00,136
Something you learned
at the abbey?

464
00:33:00,205 --> 00:33:03,038
No, it's-- um--

465
00:33:03,108 --> 00:33:04,871
um...

466
00:33:04,943 --> 00:33:06,535
rheumatism.

467
00:33:14,352 --> 00:33:18,288
Excuse me. Haven't we
forgotten to thank the Lord?

468
00:33:26,264 --> 00:33:28,824
For what we are
about to receive,

469
00:33:28,900 --> 00:33:30,834
may the Lord make us
truly thankful. Amen.

470
00:33:30,902 --> 00:33:31,891
Amen.

471
00:33:31,970 --> 00:33:33,130
[ Children ]
Amen.

472
00:33:37,409 --> 00:33:40,469
I'd like to thank each of you
for the precious gift

473
00:33:40,545 --> 00:33:42,843
you left in my pocket
earlier today.

474
00:33:44,683 --> 00:33:47,481
Um... what gift?

475
00:33:50,789 --> 00:33:53,553
It's meant to be a secret
between the children and me.

476
00:33:53,625 --> 00:33:57,288
Then I suggest that you
keep it and let us eat.

477
00:33:57,362 --> 00:33:59,660
Knowing how nervous
I must have been,

478
00:33:59,731 --> 00:34:02,291
a stranger
in a new household,

479
00:34:02,367 --> 00:34:05,768
Knowing how important it was
for me to feel accepted,

480
00:34:05,837 --> 00:34:07,805
it was so kind
and thoughtful of you

481
00:34:07,873 --> 00:34:13,607
to make my first moments here
so warm, happy, and pleasant.

482
00:34:22,187 --> 00:34:25,748
- What is the matter, Marta?
- Nothing.

483
00:34:31,997 --> 00:34:37,333
[ Children Crying ]

484
00:34:37,402 --> 00:34:40,303
Fraulein, is it
to be at every meal

485
00:34:40,372 --> 00:34:42,306
or merely at dinnertime

486
00:34:42,374 --> 00:34:46,743
that you intend leading
us all through this rare

487
00:34:46,811 --> 00:34:48,711
and wonderful new world
of indigestion?

488
00:34:49,781 --> 00:34:53,217
They're all right.
They're just happy.

489
00:34:53,285 --> 00:34:55,276
[ Crying Gets Louder]

490
00:35:05,363 --> 00:35:06,796
[ Doorbell Rings ]

491
00:35:13,205 --> 00:35:14,797
Rolfe, good evening.

492
00:35:14,873 --> 00:35:15,862
Good evening, Franz.

493
00:35:15,941 --> 00:35:17,636
I trust everything
is under control?

494
00:35:17,709 --> 00:35:18,937
Yes. Yes.

495
00:35:19,010 --> 00:35:20,136
Good.

496
00:35:20,212 --> 00:35:22,840
- Are there any developments?
- Perhaps.

497
00:35:22,914 --> 00:35:24,006
Is the Captain at home?

498
00:35:24,082 --> 00:35:25,344
He's at dinner.

499
00:35:25,417 --> 00:35:26,475
With the family?

500
00:35:26,551 --> 00:35:27,848
Yes.

501
00:35:27,919 --> 00:35:29,853
Please give him this
telegram at once.

502
00:35:29,921 --> 00:35:31,684
Certainly.

503
00:35:43,401 --> 00:35:45,835
- Telegram for you, sir.
- Mm.

504
00:35:47,906 --> 00:35:49,840
Franz,
who delivered it?

505
00:35:49,908 --> 00:35:53,344
That young lad
Rolfe, of course.

506
00:35:53,411 --> 00:35:55,470
Father,
may I be excused?

507
00:35:55,547 --> 00:35:57,481
Hmm.

508
00:35:57,549 --> 00:36:01,679
Children, in the morning,
I shall be going to Vienna.

509
00:36:01,753 --> 00:36:03,983
[ All ]
Not again, Father !

510
00:36:07,158 --> 00:36:10,286
How long will you be
gone this time, Father?

511
00:36:10,362 --> 00:36:11,886
I'm not sure, Gretl.

512
00:36:11,963 --> 00:36:14,193
To visit Baroness
Schraeder again?

513
00:36:14,266 --> 00:36:16,200
Mind your own business!

514
00:36:16,268 --> 00:36:20,671
As a matter of fact,
yes, Louisa.

515
00:36:20,739 --> 00:36:22,639
Why can't we ever get
to see the baroness?

516
00:36:22,707 --> 00:36:24,504
Why would she
want to see you?

517
00:36:24,576 --> 00:36:26,567
It just so happens, Marta, you
are going to see the baroness.

518
00:36:26,645 --> 00:36:29,876
I'm bringing her back
with me to visit us all.

519
00:36:29,948 --> 00:36:31,006
[ Children ]
Good!

520
00:36:31,082 --> 00:36:32,845
And Uncle Max.

521
00:36:32,917 --> 00:36:35,351
[ Children Shouting ]
Uncle Max!

522
00:36:50,935 --> 00:36:52,459
Rolfe!

523
00:36:55,940 --> 00:36:57,373
Oh, Rolfe.

524
00:36:59,944 --> 00:37:01,878
No, Liesl,
we mustn't.

525
00:37:01,946 --> 00:37:02,878
Why not, silly?

526
00:37:02,947 --> 00:37:03,936
I don't know--

527
00:37:04,015 --> 00:37:06,882
Isn't this why you're
here waiting for me?

528
00:37:06,951 --> 00:37:09,886
Yes, of course.
I've missed you, Liesl.

529
00:37:09,954 --> 00:37:11,387
You have? How much?

530
00:37:11,456 --> 00:37:12,650
So much
that I even thought

531
00:37:12,724 --> 00:37:14,191
of sending you
a telegram

532
00:37:14,259 --> 00:37:15,556
just so I'd be able
to deliver it here.

533
00:37:15,627 --> 00:37:19,393
Oh, that's a lovely thought.
Why don't you, right now?

534
00:37:19,464 --> 00:37:20,897
But I'm here.

535
00:37:20,965 --> 00:37:23,900
Please, Rolfe,
send me a telegram.

536
00:37:23,968 --> 00:37:25,629
I'll start it for you.

537
00:37:25,704 --> 00:37:27,899
Dear Liesl...

538
00:37:27,972 --> 00:37:29,405
Dear Liesl...

539
00:37:29,474 --> 00:37:34,411
I'd like to be able to tell you
how I feel about you. Stop.

540
00:37:34,479 --> 00:37:38,916
Unfortunately, this wire
is already too expensive.

541
00:37:38,983 --> 00:37:40,416
Sincerely, Rolfe.

542
00:37:40,485 --> 00:37:41,918
''Sincerely''?

543
00:37:41,986 --> 00:37:43,419
Cordially.

544
00:37:43,488 --> 00:37:44,921
''Cordially''?

545
00:37:44,989 --> 00:37:46,854
Affectionately?

546
00:37:46,925 --> 00:37:48,415
Mmm!

547
00:37:48,493 --> 00:37:50,427
Will there be any reply?

548
00:37:51,996 --> 00:37:54,931
Dear Rolfe. Stop.

549
00:37:54,999 --> 00:37:57,934
Don't stop.
Your Liesl.

550
00:37:58,002 --> 00:38:00,937
If only we didn't
always have to wait

551
00:38:01,005 --> 00:38:03,803
for someone to send
father a telegram.

552
00:38:03,875 --> 00:38:07,311
How do I know when
I'll see you again?

553
00:38:07,379 --> 00:38:09,813
Well, let's see.

554
00:38:09,881 --> 00:38:12,315
I could come here by mistake...

555
00:38:12,384 --> 00:38:14,818
With a telegram
for Colonel Schneider.

556
00:38:14,886 --> 00:38:17,320
He's here from Berlin,
staying with--

557
00:38:17,389 --> 00:38:20,324
No one's supposed to
know he's here.

558
00:38:20,392 --> 00:38:22,257
Don't tell your father, now.

559
00:38:22,327 --> 00:38:23,817
Why not?

560
00:38:23,895 --> 00:38:26,329
Well, your father's
so... so Austrian.

561
00:38:26,398 --> 00:38:28,332
We're all Austrian.

562
00:38:28,400 --> 00:38:30,391
Well, some people think
we ought to be German,

563
00:38:30,468 --> 00:38:33,096
and they're very mad
at those who don't think so.

564
00:38:33,171 --> 00:38:35,332
They're getting ready to...

565
00:38:35,407 --> 00:38:39,070
Well, let's hope your father
doesn't get into trouble.

566
00:38:39,144 --> 00:38:42,011
Don't worry about father.
He's a big naval hero.

567
00:38:42,080 --> 00:38:43,604
He was even decorated
by the Emperor.

568
00:38:43,681 --> 00:38:45,376
I know. I don't worry about him,

569
00:38:45,450 --> 00:38:47,714
but I do worry
about his daughter.

570
00:38:47,786 --> 00:38:49,185
Me? Why?

571
00:38:49,254 --> 00:38:50,243
Well, you're so...

572
00:38:50,355 --> 00:38:51,505
What?

573
00:38:51,638 --> 00:38:53,435
You're such a baby!

574
00:38:53,507 --> 00:38:55,202
I'm 1 6.

575
00:38:55,275 --> 00:38:58,767
What's such a baby about that?

576
00:38:58,845 --> 00:39:02,508
* You wait, little girl,
on an empty stage *

577
00:39:02,583 --> 00:39:06,451
* For fate to turn the light on *

578
00:39:06,520 --> 00:39:10,081
* Your life, little girl,
is an empty page *

579
00:39:10,157 --> 00:39:15,060
* That men will want to write on *

580
00:39:15,128 --> 00:39:21,363
* To write on *

581
00:39:21,435 --> 00:39:25,496
* You are 1 6 going on 1 7 *

582
00:39:25,572 --> 00:39:29,269
* Baby, it's time to think *

583
00:39:29,343 --> 00:39:33,336
* Better beware,
be canny and careful *

584
00:39:33,413 --> 00:39:37,406
* Baby, you're on the brink *

585
00:39:37,484 --> 00:39:41,284
* You are 1 6 going on 1 7 *

586
00:39:41,355 --> 00:39:45,416
* Fellows will fall in line *

587
00:39:45,492 --> 00:39:48,893
* Eager young lads
and rouès and cads *

588
00:39:48,962 --> 00:39:53,695
* Will offer you food and wine *

589
00:39:53,767 --> 00:39:57,430
* Totally unprepared are you *

590
00:39:57,504 --> 00:40:01,497
* To face a world of men *

591
00:40:01,575 --> 00:40:05,705
* Timid and shy
and scared are you *

592
00:40:05,779 --> 00:40:09,738
* Of things beyond your ken *

593
00:40:09,816 --> 00:40:13,809
* You need someone
older and wiser *

594
00:40:13,887 --> 00:40:17,823
* Telling you what to do *

595
00:40:17,891 --> 00:40:21,486
* I am 1 7 going on 1 8 *

596
00:40:21,561 --> 00:40:27,591
* I'll take care of you *

597
00:40:33,807 --> 00:40:35,741
[ Thunder ]

598
00:40:45,986 --> 00:40:47,920
[ Thunder ]

599
00:41:00,167 --> 00:41:03,659
* I am 1 6 going on 1 7 *

600
00:41:03,737 --> 00:41:07,229
* I know that I'm naive *

601
00:41:07,307 --> 00:41:10,572
* Fellows I meet
may tell me I'm sweet *

602
00:41:10,644 --> 00:41:14,478
* And willingly, I believe *

603
00:41:14,548 --> 00:41:18,541
* I am 1 6, going on 1 7 *

604
00:41:18,618 --> 00:41:22,110
* Innocent as a rose *

605
00:41:22,189 --> 00:41:24,123
* Bachelor dandies *

606
00:41:24,191 --> 00:41:26,056
* Drinkers of brandies *

607
00:41:26,126 --> 00:41:29,562
* What do I know of those? *

608
00:41:29,629 --> 00:41:33,156
* Totally unprepared am I *

609
00:41:33,233 --> 00:41:37,294
* To face a world of men *

610
00:41:37,371 --> 00:41:40,807
* Timid and shy and scared am I *

611
00:41:40,874 --> 00:41:44,970
* Of things beyond my ken *

612
00:41:45,045 --> 00:41:48,708
* I need someone older and wiser *

613
00:41:48,782 --> 00:41:52,411
* Telling me what to do *

614
00:41:52,486 --> 00:41:56,149
* You are 1 7 going on 1 8 *

615
00:41:56,223 --> 00:42:01,957
* I'll depend on you *

616
00:43:43,930 --> 00:43:47,331
Wheee!

617
00:43:53,673 --> 00:43:57,234
- [ Knock On Door ]
- Come in.

618
00:43:57,310 --> 00:44:00,245
Frau Schmidt.

619
00:44:00,313 --> 00:44:03,248
For your new dresses,
Fraulein Maria.

620
00:44:03,316 --> 00:44:06,251
The Captain had these
sent out from town.

621
00:44:06,319 --> 00:44:07,479
Oh, how lovely.

622
00:44:07,554 --> 00:44:09,283
I'm sure these will make

623
00:44:09,356 --> 00:44:11,153
the prettiest clothes
I've ever had.

624
00:44:11,224 --> 00:44:13,158
Tell me,
do you think the Captain

625
00:44:13,226 --> 00:44:14,750
would get me some more
material if I asked him?

626
00:44:14,828 --> 00:44:16,853
How many dresses
does a governess need?

627
00:44:16,930 --> 00:44:18,397
Not for me.
For the children.

628
00:44:18,465 --> 00:44:20,763
I want to make them
some play clothes.

629
00:44:20,834 --> 00:44:24,998
The von Trapp children don't play.
They march.

630
00:44:25,071 --> 00:44:28,268
Surely, you don't approve of that.

631
00:44:28,341 --> 00:44:31,276
Ever since the Captain
lost his poor wife,

632
00:44:31,344 --> 00:44:32,868
he runs this house

633
00:44:32,946 --> 00:44:34,345
as if he were on one
of his ships again.

634
00:44:34,414 --> 00:44:36,473
Whistles, orders,

635
00:44:36,550 --> 00:44:38,745
no more music, no more laughing.

636
00:44:38,818 --> 00:44:41,286
Nothing that reminds him of her.

637
00:44:41,354 --> 00:44:42,343
Even the children.

638
00:44:42,422 --> 00:44:44,014
It's so wrong!

639
00:44:44,090 --> 00:44:47,753
Oh, well... how do
you like your room?

640
00:44:47,827 --> 00:44:50,557
There'll be new drapes
at the windows.

641
00:44:50,630 --> 00:44:51,688
New drapes? But these are fine.

642
00:44:51,765 --> 00:44:54,131
Nevertheless, new ones
have been ordered.

643
00:44:54,200 --> 00:44:56,134
Oh, but I really don't need them.

644
00:44:56,202 --> 00:44:57,635
Good night, now.

645
00:44:57,704 --> 00:44:58,796
Frau Schmidt,

646
00:44:58,872 --> 00:45:01,033
Do you think if I asked
the Captain tomorrow

647
00:45:01,107 --> 00:45:02,074
about the material--

648
00:45:02,142 --> 00:45:04,042
He's leaving for Vienna
in the morning.

649
00:45:04,110 --> 00:45:06,135
Oh, yes, of course. Well,
how long will he be gone?

650
00:45:06,212 --> 00:45:07,645
That all depends.

651
00:45:07,714 --> 00:45:09,648
The last time
he visited the baroness,

652
00:45:09,716 --> 00:45:11,650
- he stayed for a month.
- Oh.

653
00:45:11,718 --> 00:45:13,652
I shouldn't be saying this--

654
00:45:13,720 --> 00:45:17,156
Not to you, I mean,
I don't know you that well--

655
00:45:17,223 --> 00:45:18,850
But if you ask me,

656
00:45:18,925 --> 00:45:21,155
the Captain's thinking
very seriously

657
00:45:21,227 --> 00:45:22,814
of marrying the woman
before the summer's over.

658
00:45:22,947 --> 00:45:24,608
Oh, that would be wonderful!

659
00:45:24,682 --> 00:45:26,206
The children will have
a mother again!

660
00:45:27,285 --> 00:45:31,016
Yes. well, good night.

661
00:45:31,089 --> 00:45:32,681
Good night.

662
00:45:50,775 --> 00:45:51,867
Dear Father,

663
00:45:51,943 --> 00:45:53,843
now I know why you've sent me here.

664
00:45:53,912 --> 00:45:56,312
To help these children prepare
themselves for a new mother.

665
00:45:56,381 --> 00:46:00,477
And I pray that this will become
a happy family in thy sight.

666
00:46:00,552 --> 00:46:02,315
God bless the Captain.

667
00:46:02,387 --> 00:46:03,979
God bless Liesl and Friedrich.

668
00:46:04,055 --> 00:46:08,355
God bless Louisa, Brigitta,
Marta, and little Gretl.

669
00:46:08,426 --> 00:46:11,224
And, oh, I forgot the other boy.
What's his name?

670
00:46:11,296 --> 00:46:13,730
Well, God bless
what's-his-name.

671
00:46:13,798 --> 00:46:16,232
God bless
the Reverend Mother

672
00:46:16,301 --> 00:46:18,735
and Sister Margaretta

673
00:46:18,803 --> 00:46:21,237
and everybody
at Nonnberg Abbey.

674
00:46:21,306 --> 00:46:24,002
And now, dear God, about Liesl--

675
00:46:24,075 --> 00:46:26,635
Help her to know
that I'm her friend.

676
00:46:26,711 --> 00:46:28,178
And help her to tell me
what she's been up to.

677
00:46:28,246 --> 00:46:29,736
Are you going to tell on me?

678
00:46:29,814 --> 00:46:32,248
Shh. Help me to be understanding

679
00:46:32,317 --> 00:46:34,012
so that I may
guide her footsteps.

680
00:46:34,085 --> 00:46:36,019
In the name
of the Father, the Son,

681
00:46:36,087 --> 00:46:37,111
and the Holy Ghost, Amen.

682
00:46:37,188 --> 00:46:38,917
I was out taking a walk,

683
00:46:38,990 --> 00:46:40,082
and somebody locked the doors

684
00:46:40,158 --> 00:46:41,125
earlier than usual,

685
00:46:41,192 --> 00:46:43,786
and I didn't want to
wake everybody up.

686
00:46:43,861 --> 00:46:46,261
So when I saw your window open--

687
00:46:46,331 --> 00:46:48,265
You're not going to
tell Father, are you?

688
00:46:54,906 --> 00:46:56,840
How in the world
did you climb up here?

689
00:46:56,908 --> 00:46:58,466
It's how we always
got into this room

690
00:46:58,543 --> 00:46:59,840
to play tricks on the governess.

691
00:46:59,911 --> 00:47:01,435
Louisa can make it

692
00:47:01,512 --> 00:47:03,639
with a whole jar of
spiders in her hand.

693
00:47:03,715 --> 00:47:05,307
Spiders?

694
00:47:06,417 --> 00:47:08,248
Oh.

695
00:47:08,319 --> 00:47:12,255
Liesl, were you out
walking all by yourself?

696
00:47:18,162 --> 00:47:22,292
You know, if we wash
that dress out tonight,

697
00:47:22,367 --> 00:47:23,698
nobody would
notice it tomorrow.

698
00:47:23,768 --> 00:47:26,794
You could put this on.

699
00:47:26,871 --> 00:47:28,498
Take your dress in there.

700
00:47:28,573 --> 00:47:30,837
Put it to soak in the bathtub.

701
00:47:30,908 --> 00:47:32,876
Then come back here
and sit on the bed,

702
00:47:32,944 --> 00:47:34,741
and we'll have a talk.

703
00:47:34,812 --> 00:47:36,803
I told you today

704
00:47:36,881 --> 00:47:38,872
I didn't need a governess.

705
00:47:38,950 --> 00:47:40,884
Well, maybe I do.

706
00:47:44,889 --> 00:47:47,881
[ Thunder ]

707
00:48:10,915 --> 00:48:12,109
Gretl?

708
00:48:12,183 --> 00:48:13,844
Are you scared?

709
00:48:13,918 --> 00:48:15,351
[ Thunder ]

710
00:48:17,422 --> 00:48:20,357
You're not frightened of
a thunderstorm, are you?

711
00:48:20,425 --> 00:48:22,859
You just stay right here with me.

712
00:48:22,927 --> 00:48:24,861
Where are the others?

713
00:48:24,929 --> 00:48:27,363
They're asleep.
They're not scared.

714
00:48:27,432 --> 00:48:28,990
[ Thunder ]

715
00:48:32,136 --> 00:48:34,036
Oh, no? Look.

716
00:48:35,506 --> 00:48:37,701
All right, everybody.
Up here on the bed.

717
00:48:37,775 --> 00:48:38,799
Really?

718
00:48:38,876 --> 00:48:40,309
Well,just this once. Come on.

719
00:48:40,378 --> 00:48:43,142
All we have to do is
wait for the boys.

720
00:48:43,214 --> 00:48:45,148
You won't see them.
Boys are brave.

721
00:48:45,216 --> 00:48:46,649
[ Thunder ]

722
00:48:51,222 --> 00:48:53,782
You boys weren't
scared, too, were you?

723
00:48:53,858 --> 00:48:57,726
No. We just wanted to be
sure that you weren't.

724
00:48:57,795 --> 00:49:00,161
That's very thoughtful
of you, Friedrich.

725
00:49:00,231 --> 00:49:01,664
It wasn't my idea.

726
00:49:01,733 --> 00:49:03,724
It was Kurt's.

727
00:49:03,801 --> 00:49:06,668
Kurt! That's the one
I left out. God bless Kurt.

728
00:49:06,738 --> 00:49:08,330
[ Thunder ]

729
00:49:08,406 --> 00:49:11,170
Why does it do that?

730
00:49:11,242 --> 00:49:12,641
Well, the lightning

731
00:49:12,710 --> 00:49:14,337
says something to the thunder,

732
00:49:14,412 --> 00:49:15,845
and the thunder answers back.

733
00:49:15,913 --> 00:49:17,175
The lightning must be nasty.

734
00:49:17,248 --> 00:49:18,215
Not really.

735
00:49:18,282 --> 00:49:19,510
Then why does the thunder

736
00:49:19,584 --> 00:49:20,710
get so angry?

737
00:49:20,785 --> 00:49:22,412
It makes me want to cry.

738
00:49:22,487 --> 00:49:24,682
[ Thunder ]

739
00:49:24,756 --> 00:49:27,554
When anything bothers me
and I'm feeling unhappy,

740
00:49:27,625 --> 00:49:29,320
I just try and think of nice things.

741
00:49:29,393 --> 00:49:31,258
[ Children ]
What kind of things?

742
00:49:31,329 --> 00:49:33,820
Oh, well, let me see. Nice things--

743
00:49:33,898 --> 00:49:35,058
Daffodils!

744
00:49:35,233 --> 00:49:38,225
Green meadows.

745
00:49:38,302 --> 00:49:40,736
Skies full of stars...

746
00:49:40,805 --> 00:49:42,397
Raindrops on roses...

747
00:49:42,473 --> 00:49:44,134
and whiskers on kittens...

748
00:49:44,208 --> 00:49:45,334
* Bright copper kettles *

749
00:49:45,409 --> 00:49:47,240
* And warm woolen mittens *

750
00:49:47,311 --> 00:49:49,211
* Brown paper packages *

751
00:49:49,280 --> 00:49:50,838
* Tied up with strings *

752
00:49:50,915 --> 00:49:54,942
- * These are a few
of my favorite things *
- [ Thunder ]

753
00:49:57,488 --> 00:49:58,853
* Cream-colored ponies *

754
00:49:58,923 --> 00:50:00,288
* And crisp apple strudels *

755
00:50:00,358 --> 00:50:02,087
* Doorbells and sleigh bells *

756
00:50:02,160 --> 00:50:03,855
* And schnitzel with noodles *

757
00:50:03,928 --> 00:50:05,190
* Wild geese that fly *

758
00:50:05,263 --> 00:50:06,423
* With the moon on their wings *

759
00:50:06,497 --> 00:50:10,957
* These are a few
of my favorite things *

760
00:50:12,203 --> 00:50:13,465
* Girls in white dresses *

761
00:50:13,538 --> 00:50:15,199
* With blue satin sashes *

762
00:50:15,273 --> 00:50:16,535
* Snowflakes that stay *

763
00:50:16,607 --> 00:50:18,541
* On my nose and eyelashes *

764
00:50:18,609 --> 00:50:20,042
* Silver white winters *

765
00:50:20,111 --> 00:50:22,045
* That melt into springs *

766
00:50:22,113 --> 00:50:25,549
* These are a few
of my favorite things *

767
00:50:25,616 --> 00:50:27,516
* When the dog bites *

768
00:50:27,585 --> 00:50:29,382
* When the bee stings *

769
00:50:29,453 --> 00:50:32,081
* When I'm feeling sad *

770
00:50:32,156 --> 00:50:35,387
* I simply remember
my favorite things *

771
00:50:35,459 --> 00:50:38,053
* And then I don't feel *

772
00:50:38,129 --> 00:50:42,225
* So bad *

773
00:50:42,300 --> 00:50:43,562
Does it really work?

774
00:50:43,634 --> 00:50:46,068
Of course it does. You try it.
What things do you like?

775
00:50:46,137 --> 00:50:48,071
Pussy willows.

776
00:50:48,139 --> 00:50:49,231
Christmas!

777
00:50:49,307 --> 00:50:50,672
Bunny rabbits!

778
00:50:50,741 --> 00:50:52,231
Snakes!

779
00:50:52,310 --> 00:50:53,743
Chocolate icing!

780
00:50:53,811 --> 00:50:55,073
No school!

781
00:50:55,146 --> 00:50:56,579
Pillow fights!

782
00:50:56,647 --> 00:50:58,080
Telegrams!

783
00:50:58,149 --> 00:50:59,241
Birthday presents!

784
00:50:59,317 --> 00:51:00,579
Any presents!

785
00:51:00,651 --> 00:51:01,743
Ladybugs!

786
00:51:01,819 --> 00:51:03,252
A good sneeze!

787
00:51:03,321 --> 00:51:04,413
