01:05:12,305 --> 01:05:14,739
Are you trying to say
that I'm more at home here

1055
01:05:14,807 --> 01:05:17,640
among the birds and the flowers

1056
01:05:17,710 --> 01:05:19,735
and the wind that moves
through the trees

1057
01:05:19,812 --> 01:05:21,336
like a restless sea, hmm?

1058
01:05:21,414 --> 01:05:23,075
How poetic.

1059
01:05:23,149 --> 01:05:26,118
Yes, it was, rather, wasn't it?

1060
01:05:26,185 --> 01:05:28,881
More at home here than in Vienna

1061
01:05:28,954 --> 01:05:31,445
in all your glittering salons,

1062
01:05:31,524 --> 01:05:34,084
gossiping gaily
with bores I detest,

1063
01:05:34,160 --> 01:05:36,094
soaking myself
in champagne,

1064
01:05:36,162 --> 01:05:38,630
stumbling about to
waltzes by Strausses

1065
01:05:38,698 --> 01:05:39,960
I can't even remember.

1066
01:05:40,032 --> 01:05:41,761
Is that what you're trying to say?

1067
01:05:41,834 --> 01:05:43,062
More or less, yes.

1068
01:05:43,135 --> 01:05:45,399
Now, what ever gave you that idea?

1069
01:05:48,174 --> 01:05:50,005
Oh, I do like it here, Georg.

1070
01:05:50,076 --> 01:05:52,306
It's so lovely and peaceful.

1071
01:05:52,378 --> 01:05:54,608
How can you leave it
as often as you do?

1072
01:05:54,680 --> 01:05:57,672
Oh, pretending to be
madly active, I suppose.

1073
01:05:57,750 --> 01:06:01,151
Activity suggests a life
filled with purpose.

1074
01:06:01,220 --> 01:06:04,189
Could it be running
away from memories?

1075
01:06:04,256 --> 01:06:07,089
Mm-hmm.

1076
01:06:07,159 --> 01:06:11,687
Or perhaps just searching
for a reason to stay.

1077
01:06:11,764 --> 01:06:15,894
Oh, I hope that's why you've
been coming to Vienna so often.

1078
01:06:15,968 --> 01:06:17,629
Or were there other
distractions there?

1079
01:06:17,703 --> 01:06:20,536
Oh, I'd hardly call you
a mere distraction, darling.

1080
01:06:20,606 --> 01:06:23,268
Well, what would you
call me, Georg?

1081
01:06:23,342 --> 01:06:26,243
Hmm. Lovely.

1082
01:06:27,947 --> 01:06:29,380
Charming, witty, graceful.

1083
01:06:29,448 --> 01:06:30,813
The perfect hostess.

1084
01:06:30,883 --> 01:06:33,852
And--you're gonna
hate me for this--

1085
01:06:33,919 --> 01:06:36,285
in a way, my savior.

1086
01:06:36,355 --> 01:06:38,346
Oh, how unromantic.

1087
01:06:38,424 --> 01:06:39,755
Well, I would be
an ungrateful wretch

1088
01:06:39,825 --> 01:06:41,019
if I didn't tell you at least once

1089
01:06:41,093 --> 01:06:42,390
that is was you
who brought some meaning

1090
01:06:42,461 --> 01:06:43,450
back into my life.

1091
01:06:46,098 --> 01:06:48,931
Oh, I am amusing, I suppose.

1092
01:06:49,001 --> 01:06:52,129
And I do have the finest
couturier in Vienna

1093
01:06:52,204 --> 01:06:54,001
and the most glittering
circle of friends.

1094
01:06:54,073 --> 01:06:57,440
- And I do give some
rather gay parties.
- Ho, ho, ho. Yes.

1095
01:06:57,510 --> 01:06:59,137
But take all that away,

1096
01:06:59,211 --> 01:07:04,547
and you have just wealthy,
unattached, little me--

1097
01:07:04,617 --> 01:07:08,917
- Searching just like you.
- [ Chuckles ]

1098
01:07:12,024 --> 01:07:13,286
More strudel, Herr Detweiler?

1099
01:07:13,359 --> 01:07:14,826
How many have I had?

1100
01:07:14,894 --> 01:07:15,883
Two.

1101
01:07:15,961 --> 01:07:17,895
Make it an uneven three.

1102
01:07:21,000 --> 01:07:23,025
Still eating, Max, hmm?

1103
01:07:23,102 --> 01:07:24,262
Must be unhappy.

1104
01:07:24,336 --> 01:07:25,769
That marvelous mixed quartet

1105
01:07:25,838 --> 01:07:27,362
I've been trying for
months to steal away

1106
01:07:27,440 --> 01:07:28,464
from Saul Hurok--

1107
01:07:28,541 --> 01:07:29,803
What happened, darling?

1108
01:07:29,875 --> 01:07:31,467
Yesterday, Sasha Petrie
stole them first.

1109
01:07:31,544 --> 01:07:32,875
If there's one thing
I hate, it's a thief.

1110
01:07:32,945 --> 01:07:36,278
Max, you really must try
and learn to love yourself.

1111
01:07:36,348 --> 01:07:39,044
For this, I had to call
Paris, Rome, and Stockholm.

1112
01:07:39,118 --> 01:07:40,585
On Georg's telephone,
of course?

1113
01:07:40,653 --> 01:07:43,121
Well, how else could I afford it?

1114
01:07:43,189 --> 01:07:45,555
Oh, dear, I like rich people.

1115
01:07:45,624 --> 01:07:47,091
I like the way they live.

1116
01:07:47,159 --> 01:07:48,922
I like the way I live
when I'm with them.

1117
01:07:48,994 --> 01:07:50,825
I wonder where the children are.

1118
01:07:50,896 --> 01:07:52,591
Obviously they must have
heard I was coming

1119
01:07:52,665 --> 01:07:53,689
and went into hiding.

1120
01:07:53,766 --> 01:07:56,530
I was hoping they'd
be here to welcome you.

1121
01:07:56,602 --> 01:07:58,866
Uh, Max, do step out of
character for a moment,

1122
01:07:58,938 --> 01:08:00,530
and try and be charming.

1123
01:08:09,915 --> 01:08:12,281
Well?

1124
01:08:12,351 --> 01:08:13,283
Well, what?

1125
01:08:13,352 --> 01:08:15,252
Have you made up
Georg's mind yet?

1126
01:08:15,321 --> 01:08:16,913
Do I hear wedding bells?

1127
01:08:16,989 --> 01:08:18,786
Pealing madly...

1128
01:08:18,858 --> 01:08:20,587
but not necessarily for me.

1129
01:08:20,659 --> 01:08:22,126
What kind of talk's that?

1130
01:08:22,194 --> 01:08:24,128
That is
none-of-your-business talk, Max.

1131
01:08:24,196 --> 01:08:25,390
I'm terribly fond of Georg,

1132
01:08:25,464 --> 01:08:27,591
and I will not have you
toying with us.

1133
01:08:27,666 --> 01:08:30,601
But I'm a child. I like toys,
so tell me everything.

1134
01:08:30,669 --> 01:08:33,331
Oh, come on, tell Max
every teensy weensy,

1135
01:08:33,405 --> 01:08:37,000
intimate, disgusting detail.

1136
01:08:37,076 --> 01:08:39,704
Well, let's just say
I have a feeling

1137
01:08:39,778 --> 01:08:41,245
I may be here on approval.

1138
01:08:41,313 --> 01:08:43,338
Well, I approve of that.
how can you miss?

1139
01:08:43,415 --> 01:08:44,643
Far too easily.

1140
01:08:44,717 --> 01:08:48,209
If I know you, darling,
and I do, you will find a way.

1141
01:08:48,287 --> 01:08:49,584
Oh, he's no ordinary man.

1142
01:08:49,655 --> 01:08:50,622
He's rich.

1143
01:08:50,689 --> 01:08:51,951
When his wife died,

1144
01:08:52,024 --> 01:08:53,423
she left him with
a terrible heartache.

1145
01:08:53,492 --> 01:08:54,754
And when your husband died,

1146
01:08:54,827 --> 01:08:56,852
he left you
with a terrible fortune.

1147
01:08:56,929 --> 01:08:58,988
Oh, Max, you really are a beast.

1148
01:08:59,064 --> 01:09:00,759
You and Georg are
like family to me.

1149
01:09:00,833 --> 01:09:03,267
That's why I want to see
you two get married.

1150
01:09:03,335 --> 01:09:06,600
We must keep all that lovely
money in the family.

1151
01:09:23,059 --> 01:09:24,356
What are you doing there?

1152
01:09:24,427 --> 01:09:27,828
Captain von Trapp!
I was just looking for--

1153
01:09:27,897 --> 01:09:30,092
I didn't see--

1154
01:09:30,166 --> 01:09:32,464
I mean, I didn't know you were--

1155
01:09:32,535 --> 01:09:33,502
Heil Hitler!

1156
01:09:33,569 --> 01:09:35,696
Who are you?

1157
01:09:35,772 --> 01:09:38,536
I have a telegram
for Herr Detweiler.

1158
01:09:38,608 --> 01:09:40,303
I'm Herr Detweiler.

1159
01:09:40,376 --> 01:09:41,809
Yes, sir.

1160
01:09:47,116 --> 01:09:49,949
All right, you've delivered
your telegram. Now get out.

1161
01:09:56,359 --> 01:09:58,623
Oh, Georg, he's just a boy.

1162
01:09:58,695 --> 01:10:00,094
Yes, and I'm just an Austrian.

1163
01:10:00,163 --> 01:10:01,596
What's gonna happen's
going to happen.

1164
01:10:01,664 --> 01:10:03,097
Just make sure
it doesn't happen to you.

1165
01:10:03,166 --> 01:10:06,033
Max, don't you ever
say that again!

1166
01:10:06,102 --> 01:10:08,536
You know I have
no political convictions.

1167
01:10:08,604 --> 01:10:09,730
Can I help it if other people do?

1168
01:10:09,806 --> 01:10:13,970
Oh, yes, you can help it!
You must help it.

1169
01:10:25,088 --> 01:10:26,487
Hello.

1170
01:10:29,258 --> 01:10:30,555
You're far away.

1171
01:10:30,626 --> 01:10:32,423
Where are you?

1172
01:10:32,495 --> 01:10:35,726
In a world that's
disappearing, I'm afraid.

1173
01:10:35,798 --> 01:10:38,733
- Is there any way
I could bring you back
- [ Children Chattering ]

1174
01:10:38,801 --> 01:10:41,065
to the world I'm in?

1175
01:10:41,137 --> 01:10:43,935
[ Chattering, Screaming ]

1176
01:10:44,006 --> 01:10:48,170
* Sew, a needle pulling thread *

1177
01:10:48,244 --> 01:10:50,913
*La, a note to follow sew *

1178
01:10:50,913 --> 01:10:52,210
*La, a note to follow sew *

1179
01:10:52,281 --> 01:10:56,377
* Tea, a drink with jam and bread *

1180
01:10:56,452 --> 01:10:59,387
* That will bring us back to do *

1181
01:10:59,455 --> 01:11:01,184
* Oh, oh, oh *

1182
01:11:01,257 --> 01:11:02,952
* Doe, a deer *

1183
01:11:03,025 --> 01:11:04,720
*A female deer *

1184
01:11:05,995 --> 01:11:09,328
[ Together]
Papa!

1185
01:11:09,398 --> 01:11:12,458
Oh, Captain.
You're home.

1186
01:11:20,610 --> 01:11:23,738
Come out
of that water at once!

1187
01:11:31,587 --> 01:11:35,045
Oh. You must be
Baroness Schraeder.

1188
01:11:40,163 --> 01:11:42,427
Oh, I'm soaked to the skin!

1189
01:11:47,503 --> 01:11:50,370
[ Blows Whistle ]

1190
01:11:55,178 --> 01:11:56,372
Straight line!

1191
01:12:11,294 --> 01:12:12,921
This is Baroness Schraeder.

1192
01:12:15,832 --> 01:12:18,164
And these...

1193
01:12:18,234 --> 01:12:20,395
are my children.

1194
01:12:20,469 --> 01:12:21,936
How do you do?

1195
01:12:23,472 --> 01:12:25,463
All right, go inside.
Dry off. Clean up.

1196
01:12:25,541 --> 01:12:26,906
Change your clothes.
report back here.

1197
01:12:26,976 --> 01:12:28,773
Immediately!

1198
01:12:33,249 --> 01:12:35,740
Fraulein, you will
stay here, please.

1199
01:12:37,053 --> 01:12:38,111
I, uh, ahem,

1200
01:12:38,187 --> 01:12:40,815
I think I'd better go
see what Max is up to.

1201
01:12:50,833 --> 01:12:52,198
Now, fraulein...

1202
01:12:54,570 --> 01:12:56,970
I want a truthful answer from you.

1203
01:12:57,039 --> 01:12:58,768
Yes, Captain?

1204
01:12:58,841 --> 01:13:00,741
Is it possible--

1205
01:13:00,810 --> 01:13:04,337
or could I have just imagined it--

1206
01:13:04,413 --> 01:13:06,677
Have my children, by any chance,

1207
01:13:06,749 --> 01:13:09,047
been climbing trees today?

1208
01:13:09,118 --> 01:13:10,710
Yes, Captain.

1209
01:13:10,786 --> 01:13:13,380
I see.

1210
01:13:13,456 --> 01:13:15,549
And where, may I ask,

1211
01:13:15,625 --> 01:13:18,150
did they get these--

1212
01:13:18,227 --> 01:13:19,216
Play clothes.

1213
01:13:19,295 --> 01:13:20,227
Is that what you call them?

1214
01:13:20,296 --> 01:13:21,388
I made them

1215
01:13:21,464 --> 01:13:23,056
from the drapes that used
to hang in my bedroom.

1216
01:13:23,132 --> 01:13:25,157
Drapes?

1217
01:13:25,234 --> 01:13:27,031
They still had
plenty of wear left.

1218
01:13:27,103 --> 01:13:28,434
The children have been
everywhere in them.

1219
01:13:28,504 --> 01:13:31,632
Do you mean to tell me
that my children

1220
01:13:31,707 --> 01:13:33,937
have been roaming about Salzburg

1221
01:13:34,010 --> 01:13:36,604
dressed up in nothing
but some old drapes?

1222
01:13:36,679 --> 01:13:39,341
Mm-hmm, and having
a marvelous time.

1223
01:13:39,415 --> 01:13:40,780
They have uniforms.

1224
01:13:40,850 --> 01:13:41,748
Straitjackets, if you'll forgive me.

1225
01:13:41,817 --> 01:13:43,011
I will not forgive you for that.

1226
01:13:43,085 --> 01:13:44,484
Children cannot do everything
they're supposed to do

1227
01:13:44,553 --> 01:13:45,952
if they have to worry about
their precious clothes.

1228
01:13:46,022 --> 01:13:47,114
They haven't complained yet.

1229
01:13:47,189 --> 01:13:48,281
Well, they wouldn't dare.

1230
01:13:48,357 --> 01:13:50,325
They love you too much.
They fear you too much.

1231
01:13:50,393 --> 01:13:51,951
I don't wish you to discuss
my children in this manner.

1232
01:13:52,028 --> 01:13:54,087
You've got to hear from someone.
You're never home long enough--

1233
01:13:54,163 --> 01:13:55,790
I said I don't want to
hear any more from you

1234
01:13:55,865 --> 01:13:58,925
- about my children.
- I know you don't,
but you've got to !

1235
01:13:59,001 --> 01:14:00,161
Now, take Liesl--

1236
01:14:00,236 --> 01:14:02,227
You'll not say one word
about Liesl, fraulein.

1237
01:14:02,305 --> 01:14:03,465
You're gonna wake up
and find she's a woman.

1238
01:14:03,539 --> 01:14:04,801
You won't even know her.

1239
01:14:04,874 --> 01:14:07,206
Friedrich, he's a boy, but he
wants to be a man like you,

1240
01:14:07,276 --> 01:14:08,436
and there's no one to show him how.

1241
01:14:08,511 --> 01:14:09,569
Don't you dare tell me
about my son.

1242
01:14:09,645 --> 01:14:10,907
Brigitta could tell you
about him,

1243
01:14:10,980 --> 01:14:13,005
if you'd let her get close
to you. She notices everything.

1244
01:14:13,082 --> 01:14:15,710
- And Kurt pretends he's tough
not to show how hurt he is
- Fraulein--

1245
01:14:15,785 --> 01:14:17,685
- when you brush him aside
the way you do all of them.
- That will do.

1246
01:14:17,753 --> 01:14:19,277
Louisa, I don't know about.

1247
01:14:19,355 --> 01:14:20,845
I said that will do!

1248
01:14:20,923 --> 01:14:22,481
And the little ones
just want to be loved.

1249
01:14:22,558 --> 01:14:24,753
Oh, please, Captain,
Love them, love them all.

1250
01:14:24,827 --> 01:14:26,226
I don't care to hear
anything further from you.

1251
01:14:26,295 --> 01:14:27,785
I am not finished yet, Captain!

1252
01:14:27,863 --> 01:14:29,421
Oh, yes, you are, Captain--

1253
01:14:30,733 --> 01:14:32,291
Fraulein.

1254
01:14:34,103 --> 01:14:37,402
Now, you will pack
your things this minute

1255
01:14:37,473 --> 01:14:39,407
and return to the abbey.

1256
01:14:39,475 --> 01:14:42,069
* The hills are alive *

1257
01:14:42,144 --> 01:14:43,611
* With the sound of music *

1258
01:14:43,679 --> 01:14:45,306
What's that?

1259
01:14:45,381 --> 01:14:48,009
It's singing.

1260
01:14:48,084 --> 01:14:49,642
Yes, I realize it's singing,

1261
01:14:49,719 --> 01:14:51,482
but who is singing?

1262
01:14:51,554 --> 01:14:53,181
The children.

1263
01:14:53,255 --> 01:14:56,747
*...For a thousand years *

1264
01:14:56,826 --> 01:14:58,225
The children?

1265
01:14:58,294 --> 01:15:01,695
I taught them something
to sing for the baroness.

1266
01:15:07,103 --> 01:15:09,401
*My heart wants to sing *

1267
01:15:09,472 --> 01:15:11,702
*Every song *

1268
01:15:11,774 --> 01:15:13,071
*It hears *

1269
01:15:13,142 --> 01:15:16,134
*Every song that it hears *

1270
01:15:16,212 --> 01:15:18,544
*My heart wants to beat *

1271
01:15:18,614 --> 01:15:21,777
* Like the wings
of the birds that rise *

1272
01:15:21,851 --> 01:15:25,184
* From the lake
to the trees *

1273
01:15:25,254 --> 01:15:26,446
* To the trees *

1274
01:15:26,579 --> 01:15:28,809
*My heart wants to sigh *

1275
01:15:28,882 --> 01:15:31,874
*Like a chime that flies *

1276
01:15:31,951 --> 01:15:36,752
* From a church on a breeze *

1277
01:15:36,823 --> 01:15:38,916
* To laugh like a brook *

1278
01:15:38,992 --> 01:15:41,153
- ** [ Humming ]
- * When it trips and falls *

1279
01:15:41,227 --> 01:15:43,855
* Over stones on its way *

1280
01:15:43,930 --> 01:15:45,488
* On its way *

1281
01:15:45,565 --> 01:15:50,229
- ** [ Singing Along ]
- * To sing through the night *

1282
01:15:50,303 --> 01:15:56,333
*Like a lark who
is learning to pray *

1283
01:15:56,409 --> 01:16:00,937
- * I go to the hills *
- [ Children Stop Singing ]

1284
01:16:01,014 --> 01:16:06,350
* When my heart is lonely *

1285
01:16:06,419 --> 01:16:11,482
*I know I will hear *

1286
01:16:11,558 --> 01:16:17,588
* What I've heard before *

1287
01:16:17,664 --> 01:16:22,226
- * My heart will be blessed *
- ** [ Children Harmonizing ]

1288
01:16:22,302 --> 01:16:30,539
* With the sound
of music *

1289
01:16:30,610 --> 01:16:32,100
* And I'll *

1290
01:16:32,178 --> 01:16:35,511
[ With Children ]
* Sing *

1291
01:16:35,582 --> 01:16:38,608
* Once *

1292
01:16:38,685 --> 01:16:45,750
* More **

1293
01:17:17,056 --> 01:17:18,489
Edelweiss.

1294
01:17:22,161 --> 01:17:25,426
You never told me how enchanting
your children are.

1295
01:17:34,173 --> 01:17:35,333
Don't go away.

1296
01:17:40,880 --> 01:17:41,972
Fraulein.

1297
01:17:45,718 --> 01:17:46,810
I...

1298
01:17:48,354 --> 01:17:50,322
behaved badly.

1299
01:17:50,390 --> 01:17:51,948
I apologize.

1300
01:17:53,760 --> 01:17:55,193
I'm far too outspoken.

1301
01:17:55,261 --> 01:17:56,353
It's one of my worst faults.

1302
01:17:57,397 --> 01:17:59,092
You were right.

1303
01:18:01,567 --> 01:18:04,502
I don't know my children.

1304
01:18:04,570 --> 01:18:07,903
There's still time, Captain.
They want so much
to be close to you.

1305
01:18:07,974 --> 01:18:13,207
You brought music
