Yes. It's time the children
said good night.

1559
01:32:47,073 --> 01:32:48,768
Yes, we'll be in the hall
in a moment.

1560
01:32:48,842 --> 01:32:50,469
We've got something
very special prepared.

1561
01:32:50,543 --> 01:32:51,908
- Right?
- Right.

1562
01:32:51,978 --> 01:32:53,309
Come on!

1563
01:32:59,085 --> 01:33:01,519
All that needless
worrying, Georg.

1564
01:33:01,588 --> 01:33:06,525
You thought you wouldn't
find a friend at the party.

1565
01:33:06,593 --> 01:33:09,528
A bit chilly out
tonight, isn't it?

1566
01:33:09,596 --> 01:33:11,530
Oh, I don't know.

1567
01:33:11,598 --> 01:33:14,533
It seemed rather warm to me.

1568
01:33:14,601 --> 01:33:17,968
[ Whistling Through Teeth ]

1569
01:33:18,037 --> 01:33:19,937
Ladies and gentlemen,

1570
01:33:20,006 --> 01:33:22,474
the children of Captain von Trapp

1571
01:33:22,542 --> 01:33:25,477
wish to say good night to you.

1572
01:33:38,892 --> 01:33:40,826
* There's a sad sort of clanging *

1573
01:33:40,894 --> 01:33:42,828
* From the clock in the hall *

1574
01:33:42,896 --> 01:33:46,992
* And the bells
in the steeple, too *

1575
01:33:47,066 --> 01:33:51,093
* And up in the nursery,
an absurd little bird *

1576
01:33:51,171 --> 01:33:53,935
* Is popping out to say cuckoo *

1577
01:33:54,007 --> 01:33:56,737
- * Cuckoo, cuckoo *
- * Cuckoo, cuckoo *

1578
01:33:56,809 --> 01:33:59,471
*Regretfully they tell us *

1579
01:33:59,546 --> 01:34:01,446
* But firmly they compel us *

1580
01:34:01,514 --> 01:34:03,277
* To say good-bye *

1581
01:34:03,349 --> 01:34:04,782
- * Cuckoo *
- * Cuckoo *

1582
01:34:04,851 --> 01:34:09,652
* To you *

1583
01:34:12,725 --> 01:34:15,250
* So long, farewell *

1584
01:34:15,328 --> 01:34:16,955
* Auf wiedersehen, good night *

1585
01:34:17,030 --> 01:34:19,294
* I hate to go *

1586
01:34:19,365 --> 01:34:21,026
* And leave this pretty sight *

1587
01:34:28,241 --> 01:34:30,300
* So long, farewell *

1588
01:34:30,376 --> 01:34:31,676
* Auf wiedersehen, adieu *

1589
01:34:31,676 --> 01:34:32,301
* Auf wiedersehen, adieu *

1590
01:34:32,377 --> 01:34:34,140
* Adieu, adieu *

1591
01:34:34,212 --> 01:34:35,804
* To you and you and you *

1592
01:34:43,221 --> 01:34:45,155
* So long, farewell *

1593
01:34:45,223 --> 01:34:46,952
* Au revoir, auf wiedersehen *

1594
01:34:47,024 --> 01:34:49,151
* I'd like to stay *

1595
01:34:49,227 --> 01:34:50,922
* And taste my first champagne *

1596
01:34:50,995 --> 01:34:52,428
Yes?

1597
01:34:52,497 --> 01:34:53,930
No.

1598
01:34:53,998 --> 01:34:56,091
[ Laughing ]

1599
01:34:58,002 --> 01:35:00,095
*So long, farewell *

1600
01:35:00,171 --> 01:35:01,866
* Auf wiedersehen, good-bye *

1601
01:35:01,939 --> 01:35:04,100
* I leave and heave *

1602
01:35:04,175 --> 01:35:06,109
* A sigh and say good-bye *

1603
01:35:06,177 --> 01:35:10,204
* Good-bye *

1604
01:35:13,384 --> 01:35:14,976
* I'm glad *

1605
01:35:15,052 --> 01:35:16,485
* To go *

1606
01:35:16,554 --> 01:35:19,648
* I cannot tell a lie *

1607
01:35:19,724 --> 01:35:21,749
* I flit *

1608
01:35:21,826 --> 01:35:23,418
* I float *

1609
01:35:23,494 --> 01:35:24,756
* I fleetly flee *

1610
01:35:24,829 --> 01:35:26,922
* I fly *

1611
01:35:36,641 --> 01:35:38,871
* The sun *

1612
01:35:38,943 --> 01:35:41,537
* Has gone *

1613
01:35:41,612 --> 01:35:42,874
* To bed *

1614
01:35:42,947 --> 01:35:46,713
* And so must I *

1615
01:35:46,784 --> 01:35:49,378
*So long *

1616
01:35:49,454 --> 01:35:52,150
*Farewell *

1617
01:35:52,223 --> 01:35:54,987
* Auf wiedersehen *

1618
01:35:55,059 --> 01:35:57,823
* Good-bye *

1619
01:35:57,895 --> 01:36:02,992
* Good-bye *

1620
01:36:03,067 --> 01:36:09,666
* Good-bye *

1621
01:36:09,740 --> 01:36:16,509
* Good-bye *

1622
01:36:16,581 --> 01:36:25,114
* Good-bye *

1623
01:36:29,861 --> 01:36:30,828
They're extraordinary.

1624
01:36:30,895 --> 01:36:32,988
What they would do
at the festival!

1625
01:36:33,064 --> 01:36:36,227
Oh, young lady, I must
have words with you.

1626
01:36:36,300 --> 01:36:39,360
Georg, you're not going
to let this girl get away.

1627
01:36:39,437 --> 01:36:40,768
She has to join the party.

1628
01:36:40,838 --> 01:36:41,827
No, really, I--

1629
01:36:41,906 --> 01:36:44,898
Shh. Stop it.
Georg, please.

1630
01:36:44,976 --> 01:36:46,500
You can if you
want to, fraulein.

1631
01:36:46,577 --> 01:36:48,704
I insist. You will be
my dinner partner.

1632
01:36:48,779 --> 01:36:50,041
This is business.

1633
01:36:50,114 --> 01:36:55,177
Franz, set another place
next to mine for Fraulein Maria.

1634
01:36:55,253 --> 01:36:57,346
Why...whatever you say,
Herr Detweiler.

1635
01:36:57,421 --> 01:36:59,685
Well, it appears
to be all arranged.

1636
01:36:59,757 --> 01:37:01,019
It certainly does.

1637
01:37:01,092 --> 01:37:02,286
I'm not
suitably dressed.

1638
01:37:02,360 --> 01:37:04,920
Uh, well, you can change.
We'll wait for you.

1639
01:37:08,299 --> 01:37:11,234
Captain, you must be
very proud of your youngsters.

1640
01:37:11,302 --> 01:37:12,599
I am.
Thank you, baroness.

1641
01:37:12,670 --> 01:37:14,604
Is there a more
beautiful expression

1642
01:37:14,672 --> 01:37:17,402
of what is good
in this country of ours

1643
01:37:17,475 --> 01:37:21,206
than the innocent voices
of our children?

1644
01:37:21,279 --> 01:37:23,645
Oh, come, now, baron,
would you have us believe

1645
01:37:23,714 --> 01:37:26,774
that Austria alone holds
a monopoly on virtue?

1646
01:37:26,851 --> 01:37:30,184
Herr Zeller,
some of us prefer

1647
01:37:30,254 --> 01:37:31,812
Austrian voices
raised in song

1648
01:37:31,889 --> 01:37:34,414
to ugly German threats.

1649
01:37:34,492 --> 01:37:39,088
The ostrich buries
his head in the sand

1650
01:37:39,163 --> 01:37:42,257
and sometimes... in the flag.

1651
01:37:42,333 --> 01:37:43,857
Perhaps those
who would warn you

1652
01:37:43,935 --> 01:37:45,163
that the Anschluss is coming--

1653
01:37:45,236 --> 01:37:46,897
And it is coming, Captain--

1654
01:37:46,971 --> 01:37:48,598
Perhaps they would
get further with you

1655
01:37:48,673 --> 01:37:50,971
by setting their words to music.

1656
01:37:51,042 --> 01:37:52,703
If the Nazis take over Austria,

1657
01:37:52,777 --> 01:37:54,335
I have no doubt
that you will be

1658
01:37:54,412 --> 01:37:55,811
the entire trumpet section.

1659
01:37:55,880 --> 01:37:57,177
You flatter me, Captain.

1660
01:37:57,248 --> 01:37:59,739
Oh, how clumsy of me.

1661
01:37:59,817 --> 01:38:01,409
I meant to accuse you.

1662
01:38:09,727 --> 01:38:11,957
It's very kind of you to
offer to help me, baroness.

1663
01:38:12,029 --> 01:38:13,758
I'm delighted, Maria.

1664
01:38:13,831 --> 01:38:16,299
I really don't think
I do have anything

1665
01:38:16,367 --> 01:38:18,801
that would be appropriate.

1666
01:38:18,869 --> 01:38:20,962
Now, where is that
lovely little thing

1667
01:38:21,038 --> 01:38:23,006
you were wearing
the other evening

1668
01:38:23,074 --> 01:38:25,599
when the Captain couldn't
keep his eyes off you?

1669
01:38:29,680 --> 01:38:32,808
Couldn't keep his eyes off me?

1670
01:38:32,883 --> 01:38:34,976
Come, my dear, we are women.

1671
01:38:35,052 --> 01:38:38,488
Let's not pretend we don't know
when a man notices us.

1672
01:38:38,556 --> 01:38:39,614
Here we are.

1673
01:38:39,690 --> 01:38:42,659
The Captain notices
everybody and everything.

1674
01:38:42,727 --> 01:38:45,195
There's no need to feel
so defensive, Maria.

1675
01:38:45,262 --> 01:38:47,890
You are quite attractive, you know.

1676
01:38:47,965 --> 01:38:49,523
The Captain would hardly be a man

1677
01:38:49,600 --> 01:38:51,192
if he didn't notice you.

1678
01:38:51,268 --> 01:38:55,068
Baroness, I hope you're joking.

1679
01:38:55,139 --> 01:38:57,198
Not at all.

1680
01:38:57,274 --> 01:38:59,105
But I've never done a thing to--

1681
01:38:59,176 --> 01:39:01,144
But you don't have to, my dear.

1682
01:39:01,212 --> 01:39:03,680
There's nothing more
irresistible to a man

1683
01:39:03,748 --> 01:39:05,375
than a woman
who's in love with him.

1684
01:39:05,449 --> 01:39:08,680
In love with him?

1685
01:39:08,753 --> 01:39:09,981
Of course.

1686
01:39:10,054 --> 01:39:12,022
But what makes it so nice

1687
01:39:12,089 --> 01:39:14,717
is he thinks
he's in love with you.

1688
01:39:17,128 --> 01:39:18,993
But that's not true.

1689
01:39:19,063 --> 01:39:22,931
Surely you've noticed the way
he looks into your eyes.

1690
01:39:23,000 --> 01:39:24,399
And, you know, uh...

1691
01:39:24,468 --> 01:39:28,461
you blushed in his arms
when you were dancing just now.

1692
01:39:28,539 --> 01:39:30,166
Don't take it to heart.

1693
01:39:30,241 --> 01:39:33,301
He'll get over it soon enough,
I should think.

1694
01:39:33,377 --> 01:39:34,639
Men do, you know.

1695
01:39:36,814 --> 01:39:37,838
Then I should go.

1696
01:39:37,915 --> 01:39:40,645
I mustn't stay here.

1697
01:39:50,828 --> 01:39:53,023
Is there something
I can do to help?

1698
01:39:53,097 --> 01:39:54,064
No, nothing.

1699
01:39:56,233 --> 01:39:57,564
Yes.

1700
01:39:57,635 --> 01:40:00,604
Please don't say a word
about this to the Captain.

1701
01:40:00,671 --> 01:40:05,108
No. no,
I wouldn't dream of it.

1702
01:40:11,949 --> 01:40:14,144
Good-bye, Maria.

1703
01:40:14,218 --> 01:40:17,415
I'm sure you'll make
a very fine nun.

1704
01:40:47,518 --> 01:40:49,986
Champagne, darling.

1705
01:40:50,054 --> 01:40:52,420
I feel
like celebrating.

1706
01:40:52,490 --> 01:40:54,390
Cheers.

1707
01:40:58,829 --> 01:41:00,820
You know something?

1708
01:41:00,898 --> 01:41:02,092
Perhaps.

1709
01:41:02,166 --> 01:41:03,565
Then if you're so clever,

1710
01:41:03,634 --> 01:41:05,158
tell me how to get
our little fraulein

1711
01:41:05,236 --> 01:41:07,431
to use her influence
with Georg.

1712
01:41:07,505 --> 01:41:10,338
I want those children
in the festival.

1713
01:41:10,407 --> 01:41:12,875
Elsa, this is important
to Austria.

1714
01:41:12,943 --> 01:41:15,036
It wouldn't do you
any harm, either.

1715
01:41:15,112 --> 01:41:16,739
I've thought of that.

1716
01:41:16,814 --> 01:41:19,374
Well, if it's a matter
of influence,

1717
01:41:19,450 --> 01:41:23,079
maybe the one you have
to be talking to is me.

1718
01:42:57,563 --> 01:43:12,467
**

1719
01:43:12,545 --> 01:43:27,449
**

1720
01:43:27,526 --> 01:43:42,339
**

1721
01:43:42,408 --> 01:43:57,312
**

1722
01:43:57,389 --> 01:44:12,293
**

1723
01:44:12,371 --> 01:44:27,116
**

1724
01:44:27,186 --> 01:44:41,533
**

1725
01:44:41,600 --> 01:44:48,130
**

1726
01:44:48,240 --> 01:44:51,266
- Two.
- Three.

1727
01:44:51,343 --> 01:44:53,038
Four.

1728
01:44:53,112 --> 01:44:55,410
- Five.
- Six.

1729
01:44:55,481 --> 01:44:57,881
- Seven.
- Eight.

1730
01:44:57,950 --> 01:45:00,316
- [ Grunts ]
- Four.

1731
01:45:00,386 --> 01:45:03,253
- Two.
- Seven.
- Five.

1732
01:45:03,322 --> 01:45:06,018
- Two !
- Six.
- [ Groans ]

1733
01:45:07,426 --> 01:45:09,121
[ Nervous Chuckle ]

1734
01:45:09,194 --> 01:45:11,128
Isn't this fun?

1735
01:45:11,196 --> 01:45:13,460
Um--

1736
01:45:13,532 --> 01:45:14,464
Four.

1737
01:45:14,533 --> 01:45:15,898
I'm number five.

1738
01:45:15,968 --> 01:45:17,595
Oh, yes.

1739
01:45:17,670 --> 01:45:18,602
Eight.

1740
01:45:18,671 --> 01:45:19,660
Two.

1741
01:45:19,738 --> 01:45:21,205
Four.

1742
01:45:21,273 --> 01:45:22,205
Six !

1743
01:45:22,274 --> 01:45:23,206
Ohh!

1744
01:45:24,743 --> 01:45:25,835
Two.

1745
01:45:25,911 --> 01:45:29,745
Baroness Schraeder,
do you mind if we stop now?

1746
01:45:29,815 --> 01:45:30,839
We're tired.

1747
01:45:30,916 --> 01:45:33,111
Oh, whatever
you want, dear.

1748
01:45:33,185 --> 01:45:34,846
We'll do it
again tomorrow.

1749
01:45:45,230 --> 01:45:47,494
The country's
so restful, isn't it?

1750
01:45:47,566 --> 01:45:49,625
Have some lemonade.

1751
01:45:49,702 --> 01:45:52,796
Oh, there must be
an easier way.

1752
01:45:52,871 --> 01:45:55,305
I get a fiendish delight

1753
01:45:55,374 --> 01:45:57,501
thinking of you
as the mother of seven.

1754
01:45:57,576 --> 01:46:00,306
How do you plan to do it?

1755
01:46:00,379 --> 01:46:02,313
Darling, haven't you
ever heard

1756
01:46:02,381 --> 01:46:03,973
of a delightful
little thing

1757
01:46:04,049 --> 01:46:05,983
called
boarding school?

1758
01:46:06,051 --> 01:46:08,417
Baroness Machiavelli.

1759
01:46:08,487 --> 01:46:09,784
Mm-hmm.

1760
01:46:09,855 --> 01:46:12,585
Uncle Max,
where's father?

1761
01:46:12,658 --> 01:46:14,489
I think
he's in the house.

1762
01:46:14,560 --> 01:46:17,120
What's the matter
with all you gloomy pusses?

1763
01:46:17,196 --> 01:46:18,493
Nothing.

1764
01:46:18,564 --> 01:46:20,464
I know what we'll do.
Let's have a rehearsal.

1765
01:46:20,532 --> 01:46:21,590
What for?

1766
01:46:21,667 --> 01:46:23,157
Let's make believe we're
standing on the stage

1767
01:46:23,235 --> 01:46:24,327
at the festival.

1768
01:46:24,403 --> 01:46:25,961
I don't feel
like singing.

1769
01:46:26,038 --> 01:46:28,370
Not without
Fraulein Maria.

1770
01:46:28,440 --> 01:46:30,931
Liesl, get the guitar.
Come on, Marta.

1771
01:46:31,010 --> 01:46:33,103
Everybody into the group.
You know your places.

1772
01:46:33,178 --> 01:46:34,406
Get in your places.
That's right.

1773
01:46:34,480 --> 01:46:36,414
Be cheerful.
Give us the key, Liesl.

1774
01:46:38,917 --> 01:46:41,385
Now, impress me.

1775
01:46:41,453 --> 01:46:42,977
* Ah *

1776
01:46:43,055 --> 01:46:44,022
* Ah *

1777
01:46:44,089 --> 01:46:45,386
* Ah *

1778
01:46:45,457 --> 01:46:47,220
Friedrich, Gretl,
why don't you sing?

1779
01:46:47,292 --> 01:46:49,954
I can't. I've got
a sore finger.

1780
01:46:50,029 --> 01:46:52,122
But you sang
so beautifully

1781
01:46:52,197 --> 01:46:53,960
the night
of the party.

1782
01:46:54,033 --> 01:46:56,627
Come on, all of you.
Try something you know.

1783
01:46:56,702 --> 01:46:58,329
Enjoy it. Be cheerful.

1784
01:46:58,404 --> 01:46:59,530
All right, Liesl.

1785
01:47:01,840 --> 01:47:07,642
* The hills are alive *

1786
01:47:07,713 --> 01:47:12,116
* With the sound of music *

1787
01:47:12,184 --> 01:47:16,314
*Ah ah ah ah *

1788
01:47:16,388 --> 01:47:21,519
* With songs they have sung *

1789
01:47:21,593 --> 01:47:26,121
* For a thousand years *

1790
01:47:26,198 --> 01:47:29,964
*Ah ah ah ah *

1791
01:47:30,035 --> 01:47:33,129
* The hills fill my heart *

1792
01:47:33,205 --> 01:47:35,765
* Ah ah ah ah *

1793
01:47:35,841 --> 01:47:40,642
* With the sound of music *

1794
01:47:40,712 --> 01:47:43,579
*Ah ah ah ah...*

1795
01:47:43,649 --> 01:47:45,583
They just wanted
to sing for me,

1796
01:47:45,651 --> 01:47:46,811
Bless their hearts.

1797
01:47:46,885 --> 01:47:49,080
That's lovely, lovely.
Don't stop.

1798
01:47:49,154 --> 01:47:52,123
Hmm?

1799
01:47:52,191 --> 01:47:55,058
Uh, something long
and cool, Georg?

1800
01:47:55,127 --> 01:47:57,095
No, thank you,
darling.

1801
01:47:57,162 --> 01:47:58,186
Father?

1802
01:47:58,263 --> 01:47:59,753
Yes, Brigitta?

1803
01:47:59,832 --> 01:48:01,459
Is it true
Fraulein Maria

1804
01:48:01,533 --> 01:48:02,522
isn't coming back?

1805
01:48:02,601 --> 01:48:04,466
Fraulein Maria? Yes,
I suppose it's true.

1806
01:48:04,536 --> 01:48:05,867
What have we got here?

1807
01:48:05,938 --> 01:48:07,269
Pink lemonade.

1808
01:48:07,339 --> 01:48:10,001
Laced with...
lemonade.

1809
01:48:10,075 --> 01:48:11,167
Ooh.

1810
01:48:11,243 --> 01:48:13,143
I don't believe
it, Father.

1811
01:48:13,212 --> 01:48:15,203
Hmm? Don't believe
what, darling?

1812
01:48:15,280 --> 01:48:16,577
About
Fraulein Maria.

1813
01:48:16,648 --> 01:48:18,548
Oh, Fraulein Maria!

1814
01:48:18,617 --> 01:48:21,051
Didn't I tell you
what her note said?

1815
01:48:21,120 --> 01:48:22,644
Oh, I'm sure I did.

1816
01:48:22,721 --> 01:48:25,053
She said she missed
her life at the abbey

1817
01:48:25,124 --> 01:48:26,113
too much.

1818
01:48:26,191 --> 01:48:27,658
She had to leave us.

1819
01:48:27,726 --> 01:48:30,957
and that's all
there is to it.

