trying to decide
what to give you

2116
02:04:53,666 --> 02:04:55,429
for a wedding present.

2117
02:04:55,501 --> 02:04:57,093
Oh, I know,
I'm enough,

2118
02:04:57,169 --> 02:04:59,433
but I do want you to have

2119
02:04:59,505 --> 02:05:01,837
some little trifle
for the occasion.

2120
02:05:01,907 --> 02:05:04,569
At first, I thought
of a fountain pen,

2121
02:05:04,644 --> 02:05:06,544
but you've
already got one.

2122
02:05:06,612 --> 02:05:10,343
And then I thought perhaps
a villa in the south of France,

2123
02:05:10,416 --> 02:05:13,010
but they are so difficult
to gift-wrap.

2124
02:05:13,085 --> 02:05:15,610
Georg, how do you feel
about yachts?

2125
02:05:15,688 --> 02:05:18,623
A long, sleek one
for the Mediterranean,

2126
02:05:18,691 --> 02:05:21,922
or a tiny one
for your bathtub, hmm?

2127
02:05:21,994 --> 02:05:23,120
Elsa.

2128
02:05:23,195 --> 02:05:25,755
And where to go
on our honeymoon?

2129
02:05:25,831 --> 02:05:27,628
Now, that is
a real problem.

2130
02:05:27,700 --> 02:05:30,726
I thought a trip around
the world would be lovely.

2131
02:05:30,803 --> 02:05:32,236
Then I said,
''Oh, Elsa,

2132
02:05:32,305 --> 02:05:34,296
there must be someplace
better to go.''

2133
02:05:34,373 --> 02:05:35,670
Don't worry, darling.
I--

2134
02:05:35,741 --> 02:05:37,003
Elsa.

2135
02:05:37,076 --> 02:05:38,668
Yes, Georg?

2136
02:05:38,744 --> 02:05:41,042
It's no use.

2137
02:05:41,113 --> 02:05:44,549
You and I.

2138
02:05:44,617 --> 02:05:48,713
I've been dishonest
to both of us

2139
02:05:48,788 --> 02:05:51,382
and utterly
unfair to you.

2140
02:05:55,294 --> 02:05:58,229
When two people
talk of marriage--

2141
02:05:58,297 --> 02:05:59,457
No, don't.

2142
02:05:59,532 --> 02:06:02,296
Don't say another word,
Georg, please.

2143
02:06:04,403 --> 02:06:06,667
You see, um...

2144
02:06:06,739 --> 02:06:10,175
there are other things
I've been thinking of.

2145
02:06:10,242 --> 02:06:13,769
Fond as I am of you,

2146
02:06:13,846 --> 02:06:16,406
I really don't think
you're the right man for me.

2147
02:06:16,482 --> 02:06:18,677
You're, um--

2148
02:06:18,751 --> 02:06:20,241
You're much too
independent.

2149
02:06:20,319 --> 02:06:25,188
And I--I need someone
who needs me desperately,

2150
02:06:25,257 --> 02:06:28,658
or at least needs
my money desperately.

2151
02:06:30,863 --> 02:06:33,696
I've enjoyed every moment
we've had together.

2152
02:06:33,766 --> 02:06:35,893
I do thank you for that.

2153
02:06:37,236 --> 02:06:41,468
Now, if, um,
if you'll forgive me,

2154
02:06:41,540 --> 02:06:43,804
I'll go inside,
pack my little bags,

2155
02:06:43,876 --> 02:06:46,436
and return to Vienna,
where I belong.

2156
02:06:50,716 --> 02:06:54,152
And somewhere out there
is a young lady

2157
02:06:54,220 --> 02:06:55,653
who I think...

2158
02:06:57,723 --> 02:07:00,018
will never be a nun.

2159
02:07:10,729 --> 02:07:13,323
Auf wiedersehen,
darling.

2160
02:07:39,758 --> 02:07:41,350
Hello.

2161
02:07:46,197 --> 02:07:50,463
I thought I just might
find you here.

2162
02:07:53,705 --> 02:07:56,071
Was there something
you wanted?

2163
02:07:56,141 --> 02:07:57,506
Hmm?

2164
02:07:57,575 --> 02:07:59,509
No, no, no.
Sit down. please.

2165
02:08:00,712 --> 02:08:02,145
Please.

2166
02:08:07,218 --> 02:08:09,152
Uh, may I?

2167
02:08:19,497 --> 02:08:21,658
You know, I was...

2168
02:08:21,733 --> 02:08:23,667
I was thinking

2169
02:08:23,735 --> 02:08:27,171
and I was wondering
two things.

2170
02:08:27,238 --> 02:08:32,175
Why did you
run away to the abbey?

2171
02:08:32,243 --> 02:08:33,676
And...

2172
02:08:33,745 --> 02:08:37,442
what was it
that made you come back?

2173
02:08:37,515 --> 02:08:39,210
Well, I...

2174
02:08:39,284 --> 02:08:41,184
had an obligation
to fulfill,

2175
02:08:41,252 --> 02:08:43,015
and I...

2176
02:08:43,087 --> 02:08:45,021
I came back
to fulfill it.

2177
02:08:45,089 --> 02:08:47,182
Is that all?

2178
02:08:48,693 --> 02:08:50,752
And I missed
the children.

2179
02:08:50,829 --> 02:08:52,126
Yes.

2180
02:08:53,531 --> 02:08:54,998
Only the children?

2181
02:08:55,066 --> 02:08:56,158
No. Yes!

2182
02:08:56,234 --> 02:08:58,634
Isn't it right I should
have missed them?

2183
02:08:58,703 --> 02:09:00,637
Oh, yes!
Yes, of course!

2184
02:09:00,705 --> 02:09:03,640
I was only hoping
that perhaps you...

2185
02:09:03,708 --> 02:09:06,905
Perhaps
you might, uh...

2186
02:09:06,978 --> 02:09:09,003
Yes?

2187
02:09:10,715 --> 02:09:12,148
Well, uh...

2188
02:09:12,217 --> 02:09:16,654
Nothing was the same
when you were away and...

2189
02:09:16,721 --> 02:09:20,885
it'll be all wrong again
after you leave.

2190
02:09:20,959 --> 02:09:23,655
And I just thought
perhaps you might, uh...

2191
02:09:23,728 --> 02:09:25,923
change your mind?

2192
02:09:29,801 --> 02:09:31,428
I'm sure the baroness

2193
02:09:31,502 --> 02:09:34,266
will be able to make
things fine for you.

2194
02:09:34,339 --> 02:09:35,431
Maria,

2195
02:09:36,741 --> 02:09:40,233
there isn't going
to be any baroness.

2196
02:09:40,311 --> 02:09:42,472
There isn't?

2197
02:09:42,547 --> 02:09:44,674
No.

2198
02:09:44,749 --> 02:09:46,683
I don't
understand.

2199
02:09:48,253 --> 02:09:52,690
Well, we've, um, called off
our engagement, you see, and--

2200
02:09:52,757 --> 02:09:54,691
Oh, I'm sorry.

2201
02:09:54,759 --> 02:09:55,726
Yes.

2202
02:09:55,793 --> 02:09:56,782
You are?

2203
02:09:56,861 --> 02:09:58,294
Mm-hmm.

2204
02:09:58,363 --> 02:09:59,295
You did?

2205
02:09:59,364 --> 02:10:00,331
Yes.

2206
02:10:01,699 --> 02:10:05,965
Well, you can't marry
someone when you're...

2207
02:10:08,339 --> 02:10:10,637
in love with
someone else.

2208
02:10:13,544 --> 02:10:15,102
Can you?

2209
02:10:50,214 --> 02:10:52,239
The Reverend Mother
always says,

2210
02:10:52,317 --> 02:10:54,251
''When The Lord
closes a door,

2211
02:10:54,319 --> 02:10:56,446
somewhere
he opens a window.''

2212
02:11:04,028 --> 02:11:07,464
What else does the
Reverend Mother say?

2213
02:11:07,532 --> 02:11:11,468
That you have to look
for your life.

2214
02:11:11,536 --> 02:11:14,471
Is that why
you came back?

2215
02:11:18,543 --> 02:11:21,273
And have you
found it...

2216
02:11:21,346 --> 02:11:22,472
Maria?

2217
02:11:24,549 --> 02:11:26,483
I think I have.

2218
02:11:29,053 --> 02:11:30,918
I know I have.

2219
02:11:33,057 --> 02:11:35,321
I love you.

