in the neighborhood

2293
02:20:12,352 --> 02:20:14,445
not flying the flag
of the Third Reich

2294
02:20:14,521 --> 02:20:15,681
since the Anschluss.

2295
02:20:15,755 --> 02:20:17,950
But we have dealt
with that situation.

2296
02:20:18,024 --> 02:20:20,857
Your housekeeper told me
that I would find you here.

2297
02:20:20,927 --> 02:20:23,395
It was the only information
the woman would give me.

2298
02:20:23,463 --> 02:20:25,624
What kind of information
are you looking for?

2299
02:20:25,699 --> 02:20:28,566
We want to know when
the captain will be returning.

2300
02:20:28,635 --> 02:20:30,660
Well, he's on
his honeymoon trip.

2301
02:20:30,737 --> 02:20:32,898
Uh, he's not been
in touch with us.

2302
02:20:32,973 --> 02:20:34,531
Are you asking me to believe
that the captain

2303
02:20:34,608 --> 02:20:37,475
has not communicated with
his children in over a month?

2304
02:20:37,544 --> 02:20:40,069
Herr Zeller,
how many men do you know

2305
02:20:40,147 --> 02:20:41,808
who communicate
with their children

2306
02:20:41,882 --> 02:20:43,042
while on
their honeymoon?

2307
02:20:43,116 --> 02:20:46,279
When he does return,
he will be expected to fill

2308
02:20:46,353 --> 02:20:48,184
his proper position
in the new order.

2309
02:20:48,255 --> 02:20:49,984
Naturally.
Naturally.

2310
02:20:50,056 --> 02:20:51,148
And may I
congratulate you--

2311
02:20:51,224 --> 02:20:52,987
That is, your people--

2312
02:20:53,059 --> 02:20:54,617
on deciding to allow
the festival

2313
02:20:54,694 --> 02:20:56,025
to go on tonight
as planned?

2314
02:20:56,096 --> 02:20:59,998
Why should it not go on?
Nothing in Austria has changed.

2315
02:21:00,066 --> 02:21:03,194
Singing and music
will show this to the world.

2316
02:21:03,270 --> 02:21:05,534
Austria is the same.

2317
02:21:05,605 --> 02:21:07,129
Heil Hitler.

2318
02:21:08,942 --> 02:21:11,240
Heil Hitler.

2319
02:21:12,512 --> 02:21:14,139
Come on, children,
Let's go home.

2320
02:21:14,214 --> 02:21:16,148
Why was he
so cross?

2321
02:21:16,216 --> 02:21:18,207
Everybody's cross
these days, darling.

2322
02:21:18,285 --> 02:21:20,378
Maybe the flag with
the black spider on it

2323
02:21:20,453 --> 02:21:21,647
makes people nervous.

2324
02:21:21,721 --> 02:21:23,348
Is father going to be
in trouble?

2325
02:21:23,423 --> 02:21:25,015
He doesn't
have to be.

2326
02:21:25,091 --> 02:21:26,490
The thing to do
these days

2327
02:21:26,560 --> 02:21:27,822
is to get along
with everybody.

2328
02:21:27,894 --> 02:21:29,122
I want you all
to remember that

2329
02:21:29,196 --> 02:21:30,254
tonight
at the concert.

2330
02:21:30,330 --> 02:21:31,592
Are we really
going to sing

2331
02:21:31,665 --> 02:21:33,292
before a whole lot
of people tonight?

2332
02:21:33,366 --> 02:21:34,333
Of course.

2333
02:21:34,401 --> 02:21:35,732
Look, the von Trapp
Family Singers.

2334
02:21:35,802 --> 02:21:36,928
And here are
your names--

2335
02:21:37,003 --> 02:21:38,231
Liesl, Friedrich,
Louisa, Brigitta,

2336
02:21:38,305 --> 02:21:39,897
Kurt, Marta,
and Gretl.

2337
02:21:39,973 --> 02:21:41,736
Why am I always last?

2338
02:21:41,808 --> 02:21:43,673
Because you are
the most important.

2339
02:21:43,743 --> 02:21:45,404
Oh!

2340
02:21:45,478 --> 02:21:47,105
There we go.

2341
02:21:52,185 --> 02:21:54,278
Uncle Max,
are you sure Father

2342
02:21:54,354 --> 02:21:56,618
will approve of
our singing in public?

2343
02:21:56,690 --> 02:21:58,885
Oh, he'll be pleased
and proud.

2344
02:21:58,959 --> 02:22:00,620
Liesl,
do you think so?

2345
02:22:00,694 --> 02:22:02,628
Don't
you trust me?

2346
02:22:02,696 --> 02:22:03,628
No!

2347
02:22:03,697 --> 02:22:05,289
You're a very
intelligent girl.

2348
02:22:05,365 --> 02:22:06,332
[ Laughs ]

2349
02:22:06,399 --> 02:22:08,657
Liesl! Liesl!

2350
02:22:08,790 --> 02:22:10,690
Rolfe!

2351
02:22:10,759 --> 02:22:12,624
Rolfe,
I'm so glad to see you.

2352
02:22:12,694 --> 02:22:13,661
It's been such--

2353
02:22:13,729 --> 02:22:15,026
Good afternoon.

2354
02:22:15,097 --> 02:22:16,962
You will take this, please,
and deliver it to your father

2355
02:22:17,032 --> 02:22:18,294
as soon as he comes home.

2356
02:22:18,367 --> 02:22:19,959
He's on his honeymoon.

2357
02:22:20,035 --> 02:22:21,696
- I know that.
- You do?

2358
02:22:21,770 --> 02:22:24,500
We make it our business to know
everything about everyone.

2359
02:22:24,573 --> 02:22:25,870
Who's we?

2360
02:22:25,941 --> 02:22:27,374
See that he gets it.

2361
02:22:27,442 --> 02:22:28,374
What is it?

2362
02:22:28,443 --> 02:22:30,274
It's a telegram
from Berlin.

2363
02:22:30,345 --> 02:22:32,279
Don't you want
to come over tonight

2364
02:22:32,347 --> 02:22:33,644
and deliver it
yourself?

2365
02:22:33,715 --> 02:22:36,377
I am now occupied with
more important matters,

2366
02:22:36,451 --> 02:22:39,318
and your father better be, too,
if he knows what's good for him.

2367
02:22:39,388 --> 02:22:41,219
But, Rolfe--

2368
02:22:56,538 --> 02:22:58,472
[ Children Shouting ]
Father! Father!

2369
02:23:06,081 --> 02:23:07,571
- We didn't expect you so soon.
- Hello, hello, hello!

2370
02:23:07,649 --> 02:23:11,915
When did you
get back?

2371
02:23:11,987 --> 02:23:14,319
Did you bring us
any souvenirs from Paris?

2372
02:23:14,389 --> 02:23:16,289
Hello!

2373
02:23:16,358 --> 02:23:17,791
How are you?

2374
02:23:17,859 --> 02:23:20,020
Why didn't you
telephone us?

2375
02:23:20,095 --> 02:23:22,120
We tried to, but we
couldn't get through.

2376
02:23:22,197 --> 02:23:24,461
I had nothing
to do with that, Georg.

2377
02:23:24,533 --> 02:23:26,660
We came back
as fast as we could.

2378
02:23:26,735 --> 02:23:29,067
Well, well, well,
we missed you!

2379
02:23:29,137 --> 02:23:31,071
We missed kissing you
good night.

2380
02:23:31,139 --> 02:23:33,073
We missed all the noise
you make in the morning

2381
02:23:33,141 --> 02:23:34,506
telling each other
to be quiet.

2382
02:23:34,576 --> 02:23:36,601
Mostly, we missed
hearing you sing.

2383
02:23:36,678 --> 02:23:39,340
Oh, you came back
just in time.

2384
02:23:39,414 --> 02:23:41,245
Look,
Fraulein Maria--

2385
02:23:41,316 --> 02:23:43,147
I mean, Mother.

2386
02:23:43,218 --> 02:23:45,083
We're going to sing
in the festival tonight.

2387
02:23:45,153 --> 02:23:46,051
What?

2388
02:23:46,121 --> 02:23:49,955
Yes, we've been
rehearsing all--

2389
02:23:51,860 --> 02:23:54,294
Surprise!
Surprise!

2390
02:23:54,362 --> 02:23:57,297
All right, surprises
for you on the terrace.

2391
02:23:57,365 --> 02:23:58,457
Presents!

2392
02:24:00,635 --> 02:24:02,125
We'll talk about
this inside.

2393
02:24:02,204 --> 02:24:04,229
I would have told you,
but you were away.

2394
02:24:04,306 --> 02:24:05,500
I had to make
a last-minute decision.

2395
02:24:05,574 --> 02:24:08,202
I was fortunate
to enter them at all.

2396
02:24:08,276 --> 02:24:09,402
Max.

2397
02:24:09,478 --> 02:24:11,309
They'll be the talk
of the festival.

2398
02:24:11,379 --> 02:24:14,177
Imagine,
seven children
in one family.

2399
02:24:14,249 --> 02:24:17,047
Max!
Somehow I recall

2400
02:24:17,118 --> 02:24:19,382
having made it
quite clear to you

2401
02:24:19,454 --> 02:24:21,115
how I feel about
my family

2402
02:24:21,189 --> 02:24:22,622
singing in public.

2403
02:24:22,691 --> 02:24:24,556
But the committee heard
them. They were enchanted.

2404
02:24:24,626 --> 02:24:25,957
Oh, Max,
what did they say?

2405
02:24:26,027 --> 02:24:27,961
I have never heard
such enthusiasm.

2406
02:24:28,029 --> 02:24:30,190
Oh, darling, don't you think--
Just this once?

2407
02:24:30,265 --> 02:24:32,529
Absolutely
out of the question.

2408
02:24:32,601 --> 02:24:35,001
Georg, this is
for Austria.

2409
02:24:35,070 --> 02:24:37,834
For Austria?
There is no Austria!

2410
02:24:37,906 --> 02:24:39,464
But the Anschluss
happened peacefully.

2411
02:24:39,541 --> 02:24:41,771
Let's at least
be grateful for that.

2412
02:24:41,843 --> 02:24:43,435
Grateful?!

2413
02:24:45,547 --> 02:24:47,708
You know, Max...

2414
02:24:47,782 --> 02:24:51,843
sometimes I don't
believe I know you.

2415
02:24:53,788 --> 02:24:55,949
Father, I forgot.

2416
02:24:56,024 --> 02:24:57,821
This is for you.

2417
02:25:03,109 --> 02:25:07,512
[ Door Slams ]

2418
02:25:07,580 --> 02:25:10,981
Maria, he has got
to at least pretend

2419
02:25:11,051 --> 02:25:12,018
to work with these people.

2420
02:25:12,085 --> 02:25:13,848
You must convince him.

2421
02:25:13,920 --> 02:25:16,821
Max, I can't ask him
to be less than he is.

2422
02:25:16,890 --> 02:25:17,914
Then I'll talk to him.

2423
02:25:17,991 --> 02:25:19,891
If the children don't sing
at the festival,

2424
02:25:19,959 --> 02:25:22,427
well, it will be
a reflection on Austria.

2425
02:25:22,495 --> 02:25:26,932
Oh, I know. It wouldn't
do me any good, either.

2426
02:25:32,038 --> 02:25:33,528
- Mother?
- Hmm?

2427
02:25:33,606 --> 02:25:36,166
That sounds so nice.
I like calling you Mother.

2428
02:25:36,242 --> 02:25:37,971
I like hearing it.

2429
02:25:38,044 --> 02:25:42,708
- You love Father very much,
I can tell you do.
- Very much.

2430
02:25:42,782 --> 02:25:46,445
Mother, what do you do when you
think you love someone--

2431
02:25:46,519 --> 02:25:49,818
I mean, when you stop
loving someone,

2432
02:25:49,889 --> 02:25:52,323
or he stops loving you?

2433
02:25:53,893 --> 02:25:56,327
Well, you
cry a little.

2434
02:25:56,396 --> 02:25:59,422
And then you wait
for the sun to come out.

2435
02:25:59,499 --> 02:26:00,830
It always does.

2436
02:26:00,900 --> 02:26:03,960
There's so many things
I think I should know,

2437
02:26:04,037 --> 02:26:05,937
but I don't.
I really don't.

2438
02:26:06,005 --> 02:26:07,302
How can you?

2439
02:26:07,373 --> 02:26:09,739
Sometimes I feel the world
is coming to an end.

2440
02:26:09,809 --> 02:26:11,902
And then you feel
it's just beginning?

2441
02:26:11,978 --> 02:26:13,070
Yes.

2442
02:26:13,146 --> 02:26:14,545
It was that way
with me, Liesl.

2443
02:26:14,614 --> 02:26:17,674
And for you, it will be
just as wonderful, I promise.

2444
02:26:17,750 --> 02:26:20,218
Do you really
think so?

2445
02:26:20,386 --> 02:26:23,150
* When you're 1 6 *

2446
02:26:23,223 --> 02:26:25,157
* Going on 1 7 *

2447
02:26:25,225 --> 02:26:28,922
* Waiting for life
to start *

2448
02:26:28,995 --> 02:26:31,156
*Somebody kind *

2449
02:26:31,231 --> 02:26:33,461
* Who touches
your mind *

2450
02:26:33,533 --> 02:26:38,163
* Will suddenly
touch your heart *

2451
02:26:38,238 --> 02:26:40,172
* When that happens *

2452
02:26:40,240 --> 02:26:42,674
* After it happens *

2453
02:26:42,742 --> 02:26:46,769
* Nothing is quite
the same *

2454
02:26:46,846 --> 02:26:50,782
* Somehow I know
I'll jump up and go *

2455
02:26:50,850 --> 02:26:55,287
* If ever
he calls my name *

2456
02:26:55,355 --> 02:26:59,621
* Gone are your
old ideas of life *

2457
02:26:59,692 --> 02:27:03,958
* The old ideas
grow dim *

2458
02:27:04,030 --> 02:27:05,691
* Lo and behold *

2459
02:27:05,765 --> 02:27:09,132
* You're someone's wife *

2460
02:27:09,202 --> 02:27:15,801
* And you
belong to him *

2461
02:27:15,875 --> 02:27:20,141
* You may think
this kind of adventure *

2462
02:27:20,213 --> 02:27:24,274
* Never may come
to you *

2463
02:27:24,350 --> 02:27:30,846
* Darling 1 6,
going on 1 7 *

2464
02:27:30,924 --> 02:27:36,692
* Wait a year
or two *

2465
02:27:36,763 --> 02:27:41,723
* I'll wait a year *

2466
02:27:41,801 --> 02:27:50,106
*Just wait a year *

2467
02:27:50,176 --> 02:27:51,768
* Or *

2468
02:27:51,844 --> 02:27:58,773
* Two *

2469
02:28:00,853 --> 02:28:02,150
Liesl.

2470
02:28:18,371 --> 02:28:20,305
What is it?

2471
02:28:20,373 --> 02:28:21,806
Berlin.

2472
02:28:21,874 --> 02:28:25,810
They've offered me
a commission in their navy.

2473
02:28:25,878 --> 02:28:28,210
I've been
requested
to accept immediately

2474
02:28:28,281 --> 02:28:32,217
and report to their naval base
at Bremerhaven tomorrow.

2475
02:28:32,285 --> 02:28:34,549
I knew something
like this would happen,

2476
02:28:34,621 --> 02:28:35,815
but I didn't think
it would be so soon.

2477
02:28:35,888 --> 02:28:40,825
To refuse them would be
fatal for all of us,

2478
02:28:40,893 --> 02:28:45,091
and joining them
would be... unthinkable.

2479
02:28:50,103 --> 02:28:52,765
Get the children
all together.

2480
02:28:52,839 --> 02:28:53,931
Don't say anything

2481
02:28:54,007 --> 02:28:55,941
that's going
to make them worry.

2482
02:28:56,009 --> 02:28:57,909
Just get them ready.

2483
02:28:57,977 --> 02:29:00,241
We've got to get out
of Austria...

2484
02:29:01,948 --> 02:29:03,381
and this house...

2485
02:29:06,152 --> 02:29:07,278
tonight.

2486
02:29:51,397 --> 02:29:53,831
It strains my back,
it breaks my heart

2487
02:29:53,900 --> 02:29:55,390
when I think of
a certain singing group

2488
02:29:55,468 --> 02:29:57,231
that will not appear
at the festival tonight.

2489
02:29:57,303 --> 02:29:58,463
By the time you've
made the announcement,

2490
02:29:58,538 --> 02:29:59,903
we'll be over the border.

2491
02:29:59,972 --> 02:30:02,702
I hope you appreciate
the sacrifice I'm making.

2492
02:30:02,775 --> 02:30:04,174
You have no choice.

2493
02:30:04,243 --> 02:30:07,303
I know. That's why
I'm making it.

2494
02:30:07,380 --> 02:30:10,247
Why doesn't Father
turn the motor on?

2495
02:30:10,316 --> 02:30:12,944
Because he doesn't want
anyone to hear us!

2496
02:30:13,019 --> 02:30:14,281
Shh!

2497
02:30:16,589 --> 02:30:18,489
What will Frau Schmidt
and Franz say

2498
02:30:18,558 --> 02:30:19,855
when they discover
we're gone?

2499
02:30:19,926 --> 02:30:21,393
They'll be able to
answer truthfully.

2500
02:30:21,461 --> 02:30:23,725
They didn't know anything
about it if anyone asks them.

2501
02:30:23,796 --> 02:30:25,730
Will we be coming
back here?

2502
02:30:25,798 --> 02:30:28,130
Someday, Liesl.
I do hope someday.

2503
02:30:28,201 --> 02:30:30,863
Are Father and Uncle Max
going to push the car

2504
02:30:30,937 --> 02:30:32,302
all the way to Switzerland?

2505
02:30:32,372 --> 02:30:33,304
Shh!

2506
02:30:59,332 --> 02:31:01,800
Something wrong
with your car, Captain?

2507
02:31:01,868 --> 02:31:03,358
Yes, as a matter
of fact,

2508
02:31:03,436 --> 02:31:05,370
We couldn't
get it started.

2509
02:31:07,874 --> 02:31:09,307
Kobb.

2510
02:31:11,377 --> 02:31:13,811
Fix Captain
von Trapp's car

2511
02:31:13,880 --> 02:31:16,246
so that
it will start.

2512
02:31:23,890 --> 02:31:25,824
[ Car Engine Starts ]

2513
02:31:37,737 --> 02:31:39,204
Excellent, Kobb.

2514
02:31:42,909 --> 02:31:44,376
I've not asked you

2515
02:31:44,444 --> 02:31:47,538
where you and your
family are going.

2516
02:31:47,613 --> 02:31:49,171
Nor have you asked me
why I'm here.

2517
02:31:49,248 --> 02:31:50,681
Well, apparently,
we're both suffering

2518
02:31:50,750 --> 02:31:52,877
from a deplorable
lack of curiosity.

2519
02:31:52,952 --> 02:31:57,286
You were sent a telegram,
which you did not answer,

2520
02:31:57,356 --> 02:32:00,450
from the navy
of the Third Reich.

2521
02:32:00,526 --> 02:32:02,517
I was under
the impression,

2522
02:32:02,595 --> 02:32:03,789
Herr Zeller,

2523
02:32:03,863 --> 02:32:06,093
that the contents of
telegrams in Austria

2524
02:32:06,165 --> 02:32:08,292
are private!

2525
02:32:08,367 --> 02:32:11,336
At least
the Austria I know.

2526
02:32:11,404 --> 02:32:13,235
I have my orders.

2527
02:32:13,306 --> 02:32:15,331
And they are to take you
personally

2528
02:32:15,408 --> 02:32:16,340
to Bremerhaven tonight

2529
02:32:16,409 --> 02:32:18,001
where you will accept
your commission.

2530
02:32:19,312 --> 02:32:21,246
I'm afraid that's...

2531
02:32:21,314 --> 02:32:25,751
going to be
quite impossible.

2532
02:32:25,818 --> 02:32:28,719
You see, we, uh...
all of us--

2533
02:32:28,788 --> 02:32:30,847
The entire family
will be...

2534
02:32:30,923 --> 02:32:33,391
singing in
the festival tonight.

2535
02:32:33,459 --> 02:32:35,120
As a matter of fact,

2536
02:32:35,194 --> 02:32:37,560
that's where
we were going now.

2537
02:32:37,630 --> 02:32:39,757
Couldn't possibly
let them down now.

2538
02:32:39,832 --> 02:32:41,959
I just hope
we're not too late.

2539
02:32:42,034 --> 02:32:43,763
Yes.

2540
02:32:43,836 --> 02:32:47,067
And you ask me to believe
that you, Captain von Trapp,

2541
02:32:47,139 --> 02:32:48,629
are singing
in a concert?

2542
02:32:48,708 --> 02:32:50,403
Believe me,
it will be a performance

2543
02:32:50,476 --> 02:32:52,467
beyond anything
even I've dreamt of.

2544
02:32:52,545 --> 02:32:54,740
Like you,
Herr Zeller,

2545
02:32:54,814 --> 02:32:58,215
I, too, am a man
of hidden talents.

2546
02:32:58,284 --> 02:33:01,412
Yes, um... here.

2547
02:33:01,487 --> 02:33:02,931
Program.

2548
02:33:06,601 --> 02:33:09,570
It says here only the names
of the children.

2549
02:33:09,638 --> 02:33:12,937
It says The von Trapp
Family Singers,

2550
02:33:13,008 --> 02:33:15,943
and I'm the head
of the von Trapp family,

2551
02:33:16,011 --> 02:33:17,000
am I not?

2552
02:33:19,180 --> 02:33:23,116
And these, um, travel clothes
that you're all wearing?

2553
02:33:23,184 --> 02:33:24,276
Our costumes,
naturally.

2554
02:33:24,352 --> 02:33:26,820
Herr Zeller,
this night air is not good

2555
02:33:26,888 --> 02:33:28,116
for the children's voices.

2556
02:33:34,229 --> 02:33:37,164
Well, a slight delay
in my orders

2557
02:33:37,232 --> 02:33:39,166
will not be serious.

2558
02:33:39,234 --> 02:33:41,168
Therefore...

2559
02:33:41,236 --> 02:33:43,431
you will sing.

2560
02:33:43,505 --> 02:33:45,496
You will all sing,

2561
02:33:45,573 --> 02:33:49,304
But only because that's
the way I want it to be.

2562
02:33:49,377 --> 02:33:53,313
It will demonstrate that nothing
in Austria has changed.

2563
02:33:53,381 --> 02:33:56,214
And when you
are finished singing,

2564
02:33:56,284 --> 02:34:01,813
you, Captain von Trapp,
will be taken to Bremerhaven.

2565
02:34:01,890 --> 02:34:04,757
Now, if you will all
get into your car,

2566
02:34:04,826 --> 02:34:07,317
we will escort
the von Trapp family singers

2567
02:34:07,395 --> 02:34:08,794
to the festival.

2568
02:34:08,863 --> 02:34:11,889
No escort will be
necessary, Herr Zeller.

2569
02:34:11,966 --> 02:34:12,990
Necessary?

2570
02:34:13,068 --> 02:34:14,592
Apleasure, Captain.

2571
02:34:14,669 --> 02:34:16,796
After all,
we would not want you

2572
02:34:16,871 --> 02:34:19,635
to get lost
in the crowds,

2573
02:34:19,708 --> 02:34:21,232
would we?

2574
02:34:21,309 --> 02:34:23,209
No.

